-- 1. Asana vs Monday
INSERT INTO comparisons (slug, category_slug, tool_a_id, tool_b_id, intro_content, verdict_content, migration_content, scenario_content, feature_matrix, faqs, meta_title, meta_description)
VALUES (
  'asana-vs-monday',
  'saas',
  (SELECT id FROM tools WHERE slug='asana' LIMIT 1),
  (SELECT id FROM tools WHERE slug='monday' LIMIT 1),
  '<p>Asana and Monday.com are two of the most popular project management platforms on the market, each serving millions of teams worldwide. Both tools promise to streamline workflows, improve collaboration, and keep projects on track, but they take notably different approaches to achieving these goals.</p><p>Asana leans into structured task management with a clean, hierarchical approach to organizing work. Monday.com, on the other hand, offers a highly visual and customizable workspace that feels more like a flexible operating system for teams. Choosing between them often comes down to whether your team values rigid structure or creative flexibility.</p><p>In this comparison, we break down pricing, features, integrations, and real-world usability to help you pick the right fit for your workflow.</p>',
  '<p>Choose Asana if your team needs disciplined task tracking with clear ownership, dependencies, and timelines. Its structured approach works best for teams that follow established project management methodologies. Choose Monday.com if you want a visually rich, highly customizable platform that adapts to diverse workflows beyond traditional project management.</p><p>For pure project management rigor, Asana edges ahead. For versatility and visual appeal, Monday.com wins.</p>',
  '<p>Migrating between Asana and Monday.com is straightforward thanks to CSV export and import capabilities in both tools. Monday.com also offers a dedicated Asana import wizard that maps projects to boards and tasks to items. Plan for a one-to-two-week transition period to rebuild automations and custom views that don''t transfer automatically.</p>',
  '<ul><li><strong>Marketing teams running campaigns:</strong> Monday.com''s visual dashboards and color-coded statuses make campaign tracking intuitive and engaging for creative teams.</li><li><strong>Software development sprints:</strong> Asana''s timeline view, task dependencies, and milestones provide the structure engineering teams need for sprint planning.</li><li><strong>Cross-department collaboration:</strong> Monday.com''s flexible board system lets different departments customize their views while sharing a unified workspace.</li><li><strong>Agency client management:</strong> Asana''s portfolios and workload management help agencies track multiple client projects and balance team capacity.</li></ul>',
  '[{"feature":"Free plan","category":"Pricing","toolAValue":"Up to 10 users","toolBValue":"Up to 2 users","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Starting paid price","category":"Pricing","toolAValue":"$10.99/user/mo","toolBValue":"$9/seat/mo","winner":"b"},{"feature":"Task dependencies","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Full support with timeline","toolBValue":"Dependency columns available","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Custom automations","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Rules-based automations","toolBValue":"250+ automation recipes","winner":"b"},{"feature":"Native integrations","category":"Integration","toolAValue":"200+ integrations","toolBValue":"200+ integrations","winner":"tie"},{"feature":"Mobile app","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Full-featured iOS/Android","toolBValue":"Full-featured iOS/Android","winner":"tie"},{"feature":"Customer support","category":"Support","toolAValue":"Email, chat, priority for premium","toolBValue":"24/7 support all plans","winner":"b"},{"feature":"Reporting dashboards","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Portfolios and workload views","toolBValue":"Highly visual custom dashboards","winner":"b"}]',
  '[{"question":"Can Asana and Monday.com integrate with each other?","answer":"Yes, through third-party tools like Zapier or Make you can sync tasks and updates between Asana and Monday.com for teams transitioning gradually."},{"question":"Which tool is better for small teams under 10 people?","answer":"Asana''s free plan supports up to 10 users with robust features, making it the stronger choice for small teams on a budget."},{"question":"Do both tools offer Gantt chart views?","answer":"Yes, Asana offers a Timeline view and Monday.com offers a Gantt chart widget. Both provide dependency tracking and drag-and-drop scheduling."}]',
  'Asana vs Monday (2026): Honest Comparison',
  'Compare Asana and Monday.com for project management. We analyze pricing, features, automations, and integrations to help you choose the right tool.'
);

-- 2. Jira vs Linear
INSERT INTO comparisons (slug, category_slug, tool_a_id, tool_b_id, intro_content, verdict_content, migration_content, scenario_content, feature_matrix, faqs, meta_title, meta_description)
VALUES (
  'jira-vs-linear',
  'saas',
  (SELECT id FROM tools WHERE slug='jira' LIMIT 1),
  (SELECT id FROM tools WHERE slug='linear' LIMIT 1),
  '<p>Jira and Linear represent two generations of issue tracking for software teams. Jira, the long-standing industry standard from Atlassian, offers unmatched depth and configurability. Linear, the modern challenger, prioritizes speed, simplicity, and developer experience above all else.</p><p>While Jira can be configured to handle virtually any workflow, that flexibility comes with complexity that many teams find overwhelming. Linear strips away the clutter and delivers a keyboard-first, lightning-fast interface that developers genuinely enjoy using day to day.</p><p>This comparison examines how both tools handle sprint planning, issue tracking, roadmaps, and integrations so you can decide which philosophy aligns with your engineering culture.</p>',
  '<p>Choose Jira if your organization needs enterprise-grade configurability, compliance features, and deep integration with the Atlassian ecosystem. It excels in large, regulated environments. Choose Linear if you value speed, clean design, and a tool your developers will actually want to use without being forced to.</p><p>For startups and modern engineering teams, Linear is the clear favorite. For enterprises with complex workflows, Jira remains hard to replace.</p>',
  '<p>Linear provides an official Jira import tool that maps projects, issues, statuses, and labels automatically. The migration typically takes minutes for small teams and a few hours for larger organizations. Custom fields and advanced Jira workflows may need manual reconfiguration in Linear''s simpler model.</p>',
  '<ul><li><strong>Startup engineering team (5-20 devs):</strong> Linear''s speed and opinionated workflows let small teams ship faster without configuration overhead.</li><li><strong>Enterprise with 500+ engineers:</strong> Jira''s granular permissions, custom workflows, and audit trails meet enterprise compliance requirements.</li><li><strong>Open-source project management:</strong> Jira''s free tier for small teams and public project visibility give it an edge for open-source maintainers.</li><li><strong>Product team roadmap planning:</strong> Linear''s built-in roadmap and cycle features offer a cleaner planning experience than Jira''s add-on approach.</li></ul>',
  '[{"feature":"Speed and performance","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Can feel sluggish at scale","toolBValue":"Sub-50ms interactions","winner":"b"},{"feature":"Free plan","category":"Pricing","toolAValue":"Up to 10 users","toolBValue":"Up to 250 issues","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Custom workflows","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Unlimited workflow states","toolBValue":"Simplified linear workflows","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Keyboard shortcuts","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Basic shortcuts available","toolBValue":"Comprehensive keyboard-first design","winner":"b"},{"feature":"Atlassian ecosystem","category":"Integration","toolAValue":"Native Confluence, Bitbucket","toolBValue":"Third-party only","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Git integration","category":"Integration","toolAValue":"GitHub, GitLab, Bitbucket","toolBValue":"GitHub, GitLab with auto-close","winner":"tie"},{"feature":"API quality","category":"Integration","toolAValue":"Extensive REST and GraphQL","toolBValue":"Clean GraphQL API","winner":"tie"},{"feature":"Onboarding time","category":"Support","toolAValue":"Days to weeks","toolBValue":"Minutes to hours","winner":"b"}]',
  '[{"question":"Is Linear suitable for non-engineering teams?","answer":"Linear is primarily designed for software development teams. While it can track general tasks, tools like Asana or Monday.com are better suited for marketing or operations workflows."},{"question":"Can Jira match Linear''s speed with optimizations?","answer":"Jira Cloud has improved performance significantly, but Linear''s purpose-built architecture still delivers noticeably faster interactions, especially for issue creation and search."},{"question":"Does Linear support Scrum methodology?","answer":"Linear uses cycles instead of traditional sprints, offering similar time-boxed iteration planning. However, it lacks some Scrum-specific features like story points and burndown charts that Jira provides natively."}]',
  'Jira vs Linear (2026): Honest Comparison',
  'Jira vs Linear compared for software teams. We evaluate speed, workflows, pricing, and developer experience to help you pick the right issue tracker.'
);

-- 3. HubSpot vs Salesforce
INSERT INTO comparisons (slug, category_slug, tool_a_id, tool_b_id, intro_content, verdict_content, migration_content, scenario_content, feature_matrix, faqs, meta_title, meta_description)
VALUES (
  'hubspot-vs-salesforce',
  'saas',
  (SELECT id FROM tools WHERE slug='hubspot' LIMIT 1),
  (SELECT id FROM tools WHERE slug='salesforce' LIMIT 1),
  '<p>HubSpot and Salesforce dominate the CRM landscape but serve fundamentally different audiences. Salesforce pioneered cloud CRM and remains the go-to for enterprise sales organizations that need deep customization. HubSpot entered the market with an inbound marketing focus and has grown into a full CRM suite known for ease of use.</p><p>The choice between them often reflects your company''s stage and complexity. HubSpot''s all-in-one platform gets teams productive quickly with minimal setup. Salesforce rewards investment in configuration with a system that can model virtually any business process.</p><p>We compare these CRM giants across pricing tiers, feature depth, ease of adoption, and ecosystem strength to guide your decision.</p>',
  '<p>Choose HubSpot if you want a CRM that your team will actually adopt without extensive training. Its unified marketing, sales, and service hubs make it ideal for SMBs and mid-market companies. Choose Salesforce if you need enterprise-grade customization, advanced analytics, and an ecosystem of thousands of apps on AppExchange.</p><p>HubSpot wins on usability and time-to-value. Salesforce wins on power and scalability for complex enterprise needs.</p>',
  '<p>Both platforms offer import tools and migration guides. Moving from HubSpot to Salesforce typically involves CSV exports and third-party migration tools like Trujay or Import2. Going from Salesforce to HubSpot is easier thanks to HubSpot''s native Salesforce data import. Budget three to six weeks for a clean migration with data validation.</p>',
  '<ul><li><strong>Growing SaaS startup (50 employees):</strong> HubSpot''s free CRM tier and intuitive interface let lean sales teams get started without dedicated admins.</li><li><strong>Enterprise with global sales force:</strong> Salesforce''s territory management, advanced forecasting, and custom objects handle complex multi-region sales operations.</li><li><strong>Inbound marketing-led company:</strong> HubSpot''s native blog, SEO tools, and marketing automation create a seamless funnel from content to close.</li><li><strong>Heavily regulated industry (finance, healthcare):</strong> Salesforce Shield, field-level encryption, and compliance certifications address strict regulatory requirements.</li></ul>',
  '[{"feature":"Free CRM tier","category":"Pricing","toolAValue":"Generous free plan","toolBValue":"No free CRM tier","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Starting paid price","category":"Pricing","toolAValue":"$20/user/mo Starter","toolBValue":"$25/user/mo Essentials","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Customization depth","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Moderate customization","toolBValue":"Virtually unlimited","winner":"b"},{"feature":"Marketing automation","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Built-in Marketing Hub","toolBValue":"Requires Pardot add-on","winner":"a"},{"feature":"App marketplace","category":"Integration","toolAValue":"1,500+ apps","toolBValue":"5,000+ on AppExchange","winner":"b"},{"feature":"Reporting and analytics","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Custom dashboards included","toolBValue":"Advanced Einstein Analytics","winner":"b"},{"feature":"Ease of setup","category":"Support","toolAValue":"Self-service in hours","toolBValue":"Often requires consultant","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Customer support","category":"Support","toolAValue":"Chat and email included","toolBValue":"Tiered support plans","winner":"a"}]',
  '[{"question":"Can HubSpot and Salesforce be used together?","answer":"Yes, HubSpot offers a native Salesforce integration that syncs contacts, companies, deals, and activities bidirectionally. Many companies use HubSpot for marketing and Salesforce for sales."},{"question":"Which CRM has a lower total cost of ownership?","answer":"HubSpot typically has a significantly lower TCO because it includes many features natively that Salesforce charges extra for, and it rarely requires paid consultants to configure."},{"question":"Is Salesforce overkill for small businesses?","answer":"For businesses under 50 employees with straightforward sales processes, Salesforce''s complexity and cost often outweigh its benefits. HubSpot or Pipedrive are usually better fits."}]',
  'HubSpot vs Salesforce (2026): Honest Comparison',
  'HubSpot vs Salesforce CRM compared in depth. Analyze pricing, features, ease of use, and scalability to find the right CRM for your business.'
);

-- 4. Zendesk vs Intercom
INSERT INTO comparisons (slug, category_slug, tool_a_id, tool_b_id, intro_content, verdict_content, migration_content, scenario_content, feature_matrix, faqs, meta_title, meta_description)
VALUES (
  'zendesk-vs-intercom',
  'saas',
  (SELECT id FROM tools WHERE slug='zendesk' LIMIT 1),
  (SELECT id FROM tools WHERE slug='intercom' LIMIT 1),
  '<p>Zendesk and Intercom both aim to transform how businesses support their customers, yet their philosophies could not be more different. Zendesk built its reputation on traditional ticketing and help desk workflows that scale reliably for large support organizations. Intercom pioneered the conversational approach, centering everything around real-time messaging and proactive engagement.</p><p>As customer expectations shift toward instant, personalized support, both platforms have evolved. Zendesk has added messaging capabilities while Intercom has built out ticketing features. Still, each tool''s DNA shapes its strengths and weaknesses in meaningful ways.</p><p>This comparison evaluates both platforms on support workflows, automation, self-service, pricing, and the overall customer experience they enable.</p>',
  '<p>Choose Zendesk if you run a large support operation that processes thousands of tickets daily and needs robust routing, SLA management, and reporting. Choose Intercom if you want to lead with proactive, conversational support and product engagement, especially for SaaS and digital-first businesses.</p><p>Zendesk suits traditional support teams. Intercom excels at modern, product-led support strategies.</p>',
  '<p>Intercom offers a Zendesk migration tool that imports tickets, users, and articles. Zendesk provides CSV and API-based import options. Moving help center content typically requires the most manual work. Allow two to four weeks for migration including testing of routing rules and automation workflows.</p>',
  '<ul><li><strong>High-volume e-commerce support:</strong> Zendesk''s mature ticketing, macros, and multi-channel routing handle seasonal support spikes efficiently.</li><li><strong>SaaS onboarding and product tours:</strong> Intercom''s in-app messaging, product tours, and targeted campaigns guide users through activation seamlessly.</li><li><strong>Enterprise IT help desk:</strong> Zendesk''s ITIL-aligned workflows, asset management, and SLA tracking meet internal IT support needs.</li><li><strong>Startup with proactive engagement focus:</strong> Intercom''s bots, banners, and behavioral targeting help startups convert and retain users through the product itself.</li></ul>',
  '[{"feature":"Ticketing system","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Industry-leading ticketing","toolBValue":"Conversation-first tickets","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Live chat and messaging","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Added messaging layer","toolBValue":"Native conversational platform","winner":"b"},{"feature":"AI chatbots","category":"Core","toolAValue":"AI agents available","toolBValue":"Fin AI agent built-in","winner":"b"},{"feature":"Help center/knowledge base","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Robust Guide product","toolBValue":"Articles with in-app delivery","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Starting price","category":"Pricing","toolAValue":"$19/agent/mo","toolBValue":"$39/seat/mo","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Integrations","category":"Integration","toolAValue":"1,500+ marketplace apps","toolBValue":"350+ integrations","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Reporting depth","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Advanced analytics suite","toolBValue":"Good but less granular","winner":"a"},{"feature":"In-app engagement","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Limited product messaging","toolBValue":"Tours, banners, carousels","winner":"b"}]',
  '[{"question":"Can Intercom fully replace Zendesk for enterprise support?","answer":"Intercom has closed the gap significantly, but very large support teams processing 10,000+ tickets daily may still find Zendesk''s routing, SLA management, and reporting more robust."},{"question":"Which tool offers better AI-powered support?","answer":"Both have invested heavily in AI. Intercom''s Fin AI agent is tightly integrated and handles resolution natively, while Zendesk''s AI features span across ticketing, routing, and knowledge management."},{"question":"Is it possible to use both Zendesk and Intercom together?","answer":"Yes, some companies use Intercom for in-app messaging and proactive engagement while routing complex tickets to Zendesk. Integrations between the two platforms exist via Zapier and native connectors."}]',
  'Zendesk vs Intercom (2026): Honest Comparison',
  'Zendesk vs Intercom compared for customer support. We evaluate ticketing, live chat, AI bots, pricing, and integrations for your support team.'
);

-- 5. Slack vs Microsoft Teams
INSERT INTO comparisons (slug, category_slug, tool_a_id, tool_b_id, intro_content, verdict_content, migration_content, scenario_content, feature_matrix, faqs, meta_title, meta_description)
VALUES (
  'slack-vs-microsoft-teams',
  'saas',
  (SELECT id FROM tools WHERE slug='slack' LIMIT 1),
  (SELECT id FROM tools WHERE slug='microsoft-teams' LIMIT 1),
  '<p>Slack and Microsoft Teams are the two dominant workplace communication platforms, collectively serving hundreds of millions of daily active users. Slack redefined workplace chat when it launched and remains beloved for its polished experience and extensive app ecosystem. Microsoft Teams leverages deep Office 365 integration to offer a unified hub for chat, meetings, and collaboration.</p><p>The competition between these platforms has driven rapid innovation on both sides. Slack excels at focused messaging with powerful search and workflow automation. Teams bundles video conferencing, file sharing, and Office document collaboration into a single experience.</p><p>We compare both platforms on messaging, meetings, integrations, pricing, and the overall collaboration experience to help your organization choose wisely.</p>',
  '<p>Choose Slack if your organization values a best-in-class messaging experience, needs a rich ecosystem of third-party integrations, and prefers dedicated tools for video and docs. Choose Microsoft Teams if you''re already invested in Microsoft 365 and want a unified platform that combines chat, video, and document collaboration without extra licensing costs.</p><p>For Microsoft shops, Teams is the natural choice. For everyone else, Slack often delivers a superior communication experience.</p>',
  '<p>Microsoft offers a Slack-to-Teams migration tool that imports channels, messages, and files. Slack provides workspace export features for all message history. The biggest challenge is rebuilding Slack workflows and custom integrations in Teams'' Power Automate framework. Budget four to eight weeks for a full organizational migration.</p>',
  '<ul><li><strong>Tech company with diverse tool stack:</strong> Slack''s 2,600+ app integrations and open API connect seamlessly with developer tools, design apps, and SaaS products.</li><li><strong>Enterprise on Microsoft 365:</strong> Teams'' native integration with Word, Excel, SharePoint, and Outlook eliminates context switching and is included in existing licenses.</li><li><strong>Remote-first company needing async communication:</strong> Slack''s threaded conversations, scheduled messages, and huddles support asynchronous workflows effectively.</li><li><strong>Organization with frequent large video meetings:</strong> Teams'' robust video conferencing with breakout rooms, webinar features, and town halls handles meetings for up to 10,000 attendees.</li></ul>',
  '[{"feature":"Free plan","category":"Pricing","toolAValue":"90-day message history limit","toolBValue":"Unlimited chat, 60-min meetings","winner":"b"},{"feature":"Paid pricing","category":"Pricing","toolAValue":"$8.75/user/mo Pro","toolBValue":"Included in M365 ($6/user/mo)","winner":"b"},{"feature":"Messaging experience","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Best-in-class threads and search","toolBValue":"Solid but less refined","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Video conferencing","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Huddles and clips, basic video","toolBValue":"Full-featured meetings platform","winner":"b"},{"feature":"App integrations","category":"Integration","toolAValue":"2,600+ apps in directory","toolBValue":"1,000+ apps plus Office suite","winner":"a"},{"feature":"File collaboration","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Links to external tools","toolBValue":"Native Office doc co-authoring","winner":"b"},{"feature":"Workflow automation","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Workflow Builder included","toolBValue":"Power Automate integration","winner":"tie"},{"feature":"Search quality","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Fast, accurate, filterable","toolBValue":"Improving but less precise","winner":"a"}]',
  '[{"question":"Is Microsoft Teams really free?","answer":"Teams offers a free tier with unlimited chat and 60-minute group meetings. However, most organizations access Teams through Microsoft 365 business subscriptions, which start at $6 per user per month."},{"question":"Can Slack and Teams be used together?","answer":"Yes, both platforms can coexist and even integrate through connectors. Some organizations use Slack for internal engineering teams and Teams for company-wide communication and meetings."},{"question":"Which platform is more secure for enterprise use?","answer":"Both meet enterprise security standards with SOC 2, ISO 27001, and GDPR compliance. Teams benefits from Microsoft''s security ecosystem while Slack offers Enterprise Key Management for customer-controlled encryption."}]',
  'Slack vs Microsoft Teams (2026): Honest Comparison',
  'Slack vs Microsoft Teams compared for workplace collaboration. Evaluate messaging, video calls, integrations, and pricing to choose your team platform.'
);

-- 6. Trello vs Asana
INSERT INTO comparisons (slug, category_slug, tool_a_id, tool_b_id, intro_content, verdict_content, migration_content, scenario_content, feature_matrix, faqs, meta_title, meta_description)
VALUES (
  'trello-vs-asana',
  'saas',
  (SELECT id FROM tools WHERE slug='trello' LIMIT 1),
  (SELECT id FROM tools WHERE slug='asana' LIMIT 1),
  '<p>Trello and Asana serve as entry points for teams adopting project management software, yet they offer fundamentally different experiences. Trello''s iconic Kanban boards provide a simple, visual way to manage tasks that anyone can learn in minutes. Asana delivers a more comprehensive project management suite with multiple views, dependencies, and portfolios.</p><p>Trello''s simplicity is both its greatest strength and its limitation. For teams with straightforward workflows, nothing beats the drag-and-drop satisfaction of moving cards across boards. But as projects grow in complexity, Asana''s structured approach with timelines, custom fields, and workload management becomes essential.</p><p>We evaluate both tools on usability, scalability, pricing, and feature depth so you can match the right tool to your team''s maturity level.</p>',
  '<p>Choose Trello if your team needs a lightweight, intuitive board for managing simple workflows, personal tasks, or small team projects. Its visual simplicity keeps everyone engaged without training. Choose Asana if you need to manage complex, multi-phase projects with dependencies, milestones, and cross-team visibility.</p><p>Trello is perfect for getting started. Asana is where teams graduate when they outgrow boards.</p>',
  '<p>Asana offers a direct Trello import feature that converts boards to projects, lists to sections, and cards to tasks. Attachments, due dates, and members transfer automatically. Power-Up automations in Trello will need to be recreated as Asana rules. Most small teams complete the migration in under a day.</p>',
  '<ul><li><strong>Personal task management:</strong> Trello''s boards are perfect for individuals tracking to-dos, reading lists, or side projects with minimal setup.</li><li><strong>Product launch coordination:</strong> Asana''s timeline view, dependencies, and milestones help product teams coordinate complex launch activities across multiple workstreams.</li><li><strong>Content editorial calendar:</strong> Trello''s card-based system with labels and due dates creates an intuitive editorial calendar for content teams.</li><li><strong>Multi-team program management:</strong> Asana''s portfolios and workload features give managers visibility across teams and projects simultaneously.</li></ul>',
  '[{"feature":"Free plan","category":"Pricing","toolAValue":"Unlimited boards, 10 power-ups","toolBValue":"Up to 10 users, basic features","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Learning curve","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Minutes to learn","toolBValue":"Hours to learn fully","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Project views","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Board, table, timeline, calendar","toolBValue":"List, board, timeline, calendar, Gantt","winner":"b"},{"feature":"Task dependencies","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Via power-ups only","toolBValue":"Native with timeline","winner":"b"},{"feature":"Automation","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Butler automation built-in","toolBValue":"Rules with custom triggers","winner":"tie"},{"feature":"Custom fields","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Available on paid plans","toolBValue":"Rich custom fields on paid plans","winner":"b"},{"feature":"Integrations","category":"Integration","toolAValue":"200+ power-ups","toolBValue":"200+ native integrations","winner":"tie"},{"feature":"Reporting","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Basic dashboard","toolBValue":"Advanced portfolios and workload","winner":"b"}]',
  '[{"question":"Is Trello still relevant compared to Asana?","answer":"Absolutely. Trello remains one of the most-used project tools worldwide. Its simplicity is a feature, not a limitation, for teams that don''t need complex project management overhead."},{"question":"Can I use Trello inside Asana or vice versa?","answer":"While there''s no native embed, you can sync data between Trello and Asana using Zapier or Unito, allowing teams to work in their preferred tool while sharing updates."},{"question":"Which tool scales better for growing teams?","answer":"Asana scales better for growing organizations. Its portfolios, goals, and workload management features become increasingly valuable as teams and project complexity grow."}]',
  'Trello vs Asana (2026): Honest Comparison',
  'Trello vs Asana compared for project management. We evaluate simplicity vs power, pricing, views, and features to help you choose the right tool.'
);

-- 7. ClickUp vs Monday
INSERT INTO comparisons (slug, category_slug, tool_a_id, tool_b_id, intro_content, verdict_content, migration_content, scenario_content, feature_matrix, faqs, meta_title, meta_description)
VALUES (
  'clickup-vs-monday',
  'saas',
  (SELECT id FROM tools WHERE slug='clickup' LIMIT 1),
  (SELECT id FROM tools WHERE slug='monday' LIMIT 1),
  '<p>ClickUp and Monday.com compete head-to-head as all-in-one productivity platforms that aim to replace your entire tool stack. ClickUp brands itself as "one app to replace them all" with an aggressive feature set that includes docs, whiteboards, goals, and time tracking alongside project management. Monday.com focuses on being a flexible work operating system with exceptional visual customization.</p><p>Both platforms have expanded rapidly, adding AI features, CRM capabilities, and advanced automations. ClickUp tends to pack more features into its free and lower-tier plans. Monday.com often delivers a more polished, intuitive experience with each individual feature it offers.</p><p>This comparison helps you decide whether feature density or design polish matters more for your team''s daily workflows.</p>',
  '<p>Choose ClickUp if you want maximum features at minimum cost and your team can handle a steeper learning curve. Its free plan is remarkably generous. Choose Monday.com if your team values intuitive design, visual workflows, and a platform that non-technical members will adopt enthusiastically.</p><p>ClickUp wins on value and feature count. Monday.com wins on user experience and visual appeal.</p>',
  '<p>Both platforms offer import tools for common competitors and CSV imports. ClickUp has a native Monday.com import feature that maps boards to spaces and items to tasks. Moving automations and custom integrations requires manual rebuilding on either side. Plan for one to two weeks of setup and team training.</p>',
  '<ul><li><strong>Budget-conscious startup:</strong> ClickUp''s free tier with unlimited tasks, members, and 100MB storage outperforms Monday.com''s limited free plan significantly.</li><li><strong>Design and creative agency:</strong> Monday.com''s visual boards, proofing features, and creative workflow templates resonate with design-oriented teams.</li><li><strong>All-in-one replacement strategy:</strong> ClickUp''s built-in docs, whiteboards, goals, and chat reduce the need for separate Notion, Miro, or Slack subscriptions.</li><li><strong>Client-facing project dashboards:</strong> Monday.com''s shareable dashboards and guest access make it easy to give clients polished project visibility.</li></ul>',
  '[{"feature":"Free plan","category":"Pricing","toolAValue":"Unlimited users and tasks","toolBValue":"Up to 2 users only","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Paid starting price","category":"Pricing","toolAValue":"$7/user/mo","toolBValue":"$9/seat/mo","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Built-in docs","category":"Core","toolAValue":"ClickUp Docs included","toolBValue":"WorkDocs included","winner":"tie"},{"feature":"Time tracking","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Native time tracking free","toolBValue":"Requires paid add-on","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Whiteboards","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Built-in whiteboards","toolBValue":"Basic whiteboard feature","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Visual customization","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Functional but dense UI","toolBValue":"Highly visual, color-coded","winner":"b"},{"feature":"Automation limit","category":"Core","toolAValue":"100/mo on free, 10K+ on paid","toolBValue":"250/mo on paid plans","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Customer support","category":"Support","toolAValue":"24/7 chat and email","toolBValue":"24/7 support all plans","winner":"tie"}]',
  '[{"question":"Which platform has better AI features?","answer":"Both have introduced AI assistants. ClickUp AI helps with writing, summarization, and task creation. Monday AI assists with formula building, content generation, and status updates. Both are rapidly evolving."},{"question":"Is ClickUp too complex for non-technical teams?","answer":"ClickUp''s feature density can overwhelm new users. However, you can simplify the interface by disabling unused features in ClickApps settings, making it more approachable for non-technical teams."},{"question":"Can either tool replace a CRM?","answer":"Both offer CRM templates and features. Monday.com''s dedicated CRM product is more mature, while ClickUp''s CRM capabilities work well for simple sales pipelines but lack advanced CRM functionality."}]',
  'ClickUp vs Monday (2026): Honest Comparison',
  'ClickUp vs Monday.com compared for productivity. We analyze free plans, features, pricing, and usability to help you choose your work management platform.'
);

-- 8. Notion vs ClickUp
INSERT INTO comparisons (slug, category_slug, tool_a_id, tool_b_id, intro_content, verdict_content, migration_content, scenario_content, feature_matrix, faqs, meta_title, meta_description)
VALUES (
  'notion-vs-clickup',
  'saas',
  (SELECT id FROM tools WHERE slug='notion' LIMIT 1),
  (SELECT id FROM tools WHERE slug='clickup' LIMIT 1),
  '<p>Notion and ClickUp both aim to consolidate your workspace into a single platform, but they approach this goal from opposite directions. Notion starts as a flexible knowledge management and documentation tool that can be shaped into a project manager. ClickUp starts as a powerful project management platform that has added docs and wikis to its arsenal.</p><p>Notion''s block-based editor and linked databases give it unmatched flexibility for building custom wikis, processes, and lightweight project tracking. ClickUp''s structured hierarchy of spaces, folders, lists, and tasks provides more opinionated project management out of the box.</p><p>We compare these all-in-one tools across documentation, project management, collaboration, and pricing to help you determine which foundation better serves your team.</p>',
  '<p>Choose Notion if documentation, knowledge management, and flexible databases are your primary needs, with light project management as a secondary concern. Choose ClickUp if you need robust project management with task dependencies, time tracking, and Gantt charts, and documentation is supplementary.</p><p>Notion is a wiki that does project management. ClickUp is a project manager that does wikis. Pick the core need.</p>',
  '<p>ClickUp supports importing from Notion through a native connector that brings over pages and databases. Notion can import from various formats including CSV and Markdown. The conceptual mapping is the challenge: Notion databases don''t map cleanly to ClickUp''s hierarchy, and ClickUp tasks lose their structure in Notion''s freeform pages.</p>',
  '<ul><li><strong>Company knowledge base and wiki:</strong> Notion''s nested pages, templates, and linked databases create superior internal documentation systems.</li><li><strong>Software development sprints:</strong> ClickUp''s sprint management, bug tracking, and Git integrations serve engineering workflows better than Notion''s manual setups.</li><li><strong>Product requirements and specs:</strong> Notion''s rich text editing and database relations let product teams create interconnected PRDs, specs, and roadmaps beautifully.</li><li><strong>Agency project delivery:</strong> ClickUp''s time tracking, workload management, and client permissions handle agency workflows with built-in accountability.</li></ul>',
  '[{"feature":"Documentation quality","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Best-in-class block editor","toolBValue":"Good but less flexible","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Project management depth","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Basic via databases","toolBValue":"Full PM suite with Gantt, deps","winner":"b"},{"feature":"Free plan","category":"Pricing","toolAValue":"Generous for individuals","toolBValue":"Unlimited users and tasks","winner":"b"},{"feature":"Database/relations","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Powerful linked databases","toolBValue":"Custom fields and relations","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Time tracking","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Not available natively","toolBValue":"Built-in free time tracking","winner":"b"},{"feature":"Templates","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Huge community template gallery","toolBValue":"Extensive built-in templates","winner":"tie"},{"feature":"API and integrations","category":"Integration","toolAValue":"Clean API, growing integrations","toolBValue":"1,000+ integrations","winner":"b"},{"feature":"Mobile experience","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Solid mobile app","toolBValue":"Feature-rich but complex mobile app","winner":"a"}]',
  '[{"question":"Can Notion replace ClickUp for project management?","answer":"For simple project tracking with databases and boards, yes. But teams needing dependencies, Gantt charts, time tracking, sprint management, and workload balancing will find Notion''s capabilities insufficient."},{"question":"Which tool is better for a team wiki?","answer":"Notion is significantly better for wikis and documentation. Its block editor, nested pages, and synced databases create a more natural and powerful knowledge management experience."},{"question":"Do both tools offer AI features?","answer":"Yes. Notion AI helps with writing, summarizing, and autofilling database properties. ClickUp AI assists with task creation, writing, and project summaries. Both charge extra for AI features."}]',
  'Notion vs ClickUp (2026): Honest Comparison',
  'Notion vs ClickUp compared as all-in-one workspaces. We evaluate docs, project management, pricing, and flexibility to help you choose.'
);

-- 9. Pipedrive vs HubSpot
INSERT INTO comparisons (slug, category_slug, tool_a_id, tool_b_id, intro_content, verdict_content, migration_content, scenario_content, feature_matrix, faqs, meta_title, meta_description)
VALUES (
  'pipedrive-vs-hubspot',
  'saas',
  (SELECT id FROM tools WHERE slug='pipedrive' LIMIT 1),
  (SELECT id FROM tools WHERE slug='hubspot' LIMIT 1),
  '<p>Pipedrive and HubSpot are both widely adopted CRM platforms, but they serve different types of sales organizations. Pipedrive is a sales-focused CRM built by salespeople for salespeople, emphasizing pipeline visibility and deal management above all else. HubSpot is a broader platform spanning marketing, sales, service, and CMS under one roof.</p><p>Pipedrive''s laser focus on the sales pipeline makes it incredibly intuitive for reps who want to spend time selling, not configuring software. HubSpot''s breadth means marketing and sales teams share a single source of truth, but that comprehensiveness adds complexity and cost at higher tiers.</p><p>We compare these CRMs on pipeline management, automation, pricing, and how well they serve different sales team structures and strategies.</p>',
  '<p>Choose Pipedrive if you want a straightforward, sales-first CRM that your reps will adopt immediately. Its visual pipeline and activity-based selling approach keep deals moving forward. Choose HubSpot if you need marketing automation, content management, and customer service alongside your CRM in a unified ecosystem.</p><p>Pipedrive wins for dedicated sales teams. HubSpot wins for companies wanting an all-in-one growth platform.</p>',
  '<p>HubSpot offers a Pipedrive import tool that maps pipelines to deal stages and syncs contacts and activities. Pipedrive supports CSV imports from any CRM. The main challenge is recreating email sequences and automation workflows since they don''t transfer between platforms. Allow one to three weeks depending on data volume and complexity.</p>',
  '<ul><li><strong>Small sales team (3-10 reps):</strong> Pipedrive''s intuitive pipeline view and activity reminders keep small teams focused on closing deals without administrative overhead.</li><li><strong>Marketing-driven SaaS company:</strong> HubSpot''s integrated marketing hub with landing pages, email campaigns, and lead scoring feeds qualified leads directly into the sales pipeline.</li><li><strong>Outbound sales organization:</strong> Pipedrive''s email tracking, call logging, and prospector tool support outbound sales motions efficiently at a lower cost.</li><li><strong>Company scaling from 50 to 500 employees:</strong> HubSpot''s operational hub, custom objects, and advanced permissions scale with organizational complexity better than Pipedrive.</li></ul>',
  '[{"feature":"Starting price","category":"Pricing","toolAValue":"$14/user/mo Essential","toolBValue":"Free CRM, $20/user/mo Starter","winner":"b"},{"feature":"Pipeline visualization","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Best-in-class visual pipeline","toolBValue":"Standard deal board","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Marketing tools","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Basic email campaigns","toolBValue":"Full marketing automation suite","winner":"b"},{"feature":"Activity-based selling","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Core philosophy of the CRM","toolBValue":"Activity tracking available","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Email sequences","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Built-in email automation","toolBValue":"Sequences in Sales Hub","winner":"tie"},{"feature":"Reporting","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Sales-focused dashboards","toolBValue":"Cross-functional reporting","winner":"b"},{"feature":"Integrations","category":"Integration","toolAValue":"400+ integrations","toolBValue":"1,500+ integrations","winner":"b"},{"feature":"Ease of setup","category":"Support","toolAValue":"Live in 30 minutes","toolBValue":"Simple for basics, complex at scale","winner":"a"}]',
  '[{"question":"Is Pipedrive only for small businesses?","answer":"No. Pipedrive serves teams of all sizes, including companies with hundreds of sales reps. However, organizations needing integrated marketing and service hubs may outgrow Pipedrive''s sales-only focus."},{"question":"Can I use Pipedrive with HubSpot Marketing?","answer":"Yes, through native and Zapier integrations. Some companies use HubSpot for marketing lead generation and Pipedrive for sales pipeline management, syncing contacts between the two."},{"question":"Which CRM has better email features?","answer":"HubSpot offers more comprehensive email marketing with templates, A/B testing, and smart send times. Pipedrive focuses on one-to-one sales emails with tracking and basic sequence automation."}]',
  'Pipedrive vs HubSpot (2026): Honest Comparison',
  'Pipedrive vs HubSpot CRM compared for sales teams. We analyze pipeline management, pricing, marketing features, and ease of use in this guide.'
);

-- 10. Freshdesk vs Zendesk
INSERT INTO comparisons (slug, category_slug, tool_a_id, tool_b_id, intro_content, verdict_content, migration_content, scenario_content, feature_matrix, faqs, meta_title, meta_description)
VALUES (
  'freshdesk-vs-zendesk',
  'saas',
  (SELECT id FROM tools WHERE slug='freshdesk' LIMIT 1),
  (SELECT id FROM tools WHERE slug='zendesk' LIMIT 1),
  '<p>Freshdesk and Zendesk are the two most frequently compared help desk platforms, and for good reason. Zendesk is the established market leader with deep enterprise capabilities and a vast ecosystem. Freshdesk, from Freshworks, positions itself as the value-driven alternative with comparable features at significantly lower prices.</p><p>Both platforms cover ticketing, knowledge bases, live chat, automation, and multi-channel support. The differences emerge in pricing philosophy, ease of administration, and how far each tool extends into adjacent business functions like CRM and IT management.</p><p>This comparison examines feature parity, real-world pricing differences, customer satisfaction, and integration ecosystems to determine which help desk delivers better value for your support operation.</p>',
  '<p>Choose Freshdesk if you want enterprise-grade help desk features at a fraction of Zendesk''s price, especially if you''re exploring the broader Freshworks ecosystem for CRM and ITSM. Choose Zendesk if you need the deepest integration marketplace, most mature analytics, and battle-tested scalability for very large support organizations.</p><p>Freshdesk wins on value. Zendesk wins on ecosystem maturity and enterprise depth.</p>',
  '<p>Freshdesk provides a Zendesk migration tool that imports tickets, contacts, agents, knowledge base articles, and satisfaction ratings. Zendesk supports imports via API and CSV. Routing rules and macros need manual recreation. Most mid-size teams complete the migration in one to two weeks with proper planning.</p>',
  '<ul><li><strong>Cost-conscious growing company:</strong> Freshdesk''s free plan for up to 10 agents and competitive paid tiers make it ideal for teams watching their support budget.</li><li><strong>Enterprise with complex requirements:</strong> Zendesk''s advanced routing, custom ticket statuses, and Sunshine platform handle sophisticated enterprise support workflows.</li><li><strong>Company using Freshworks suite:</strong> Freshdesk integrates natively with Freshsales, Freshchat, and Freshservice, creating a unified customer engagement platform.</li><li><strong>Organization needing deep third-party integrations:</strong> Zendesk''s marketplace of 1,500+ apps provides pre-built connections to virtually any business tool.</li></ul>',
  '[{"feature":"Free plan","category":"Pricing","toolAValue":"Up to 10 agents","toolBValue":"No free plan","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Paid starting price","category":"Pricing","toolAValue":"$15/agent/mo Growth","toolBValue":"$19/agent/mo Support Team","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Ticketing system","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Full-featured ticketing","toolBValue":"Industry-leading ticketing","winner":"b"},{"feature":"Knowledge base","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Included on all plans","toolBValue":"Guide product, paid add-on","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Marketplace apps","category":"Integration","toolAValue":"1,000+ apps","toolBValue":"1,500+ apps","winner":"b"},{"feature":"AI capabilities","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Freddy AI agent","toolBValue":"Advanced AI across suite","winner":"b"},{"feature":"Multi-channel support","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Email, chat, phone, social","toolBValue":"Email, chat, phone, social, messaging","winner":"tie"},{"feature":"Admin complexity","category":"Support","toolAValue":"Intuitive admin panel","toolBValue":"Steeper admin learning curve","winner":"a"}]',
  '[{"question":"Is Freshdesk as reliable as Zendesk for large teams?","answer":"Freshdesk handles large support operations well, with clients processing millions of tickets. However, Zendesk''s longer track record at extreme scale gives some enterprise teams more confidence."},{"question":"Which platform has better gamification features?","answer":"Freshdesk includes built-in gamification called Freshdesk Arcade with leaderboards, badges, and quests to motivate agents. Zendesk lacks native gamification and requires third-party apps."},{"question":"Can I switch from Zendesk to Freshdesk without losing data?","answer":"Yes. Freshdesk''s migration tool preserves ticket history, customer data, and knowledge base content. Satisfaction ratings and basic automations also transfer, though complex triggers need manual setup."}]',
  'Freshdesk vs Zendesk (2026): Honest Comparison',
  'Freshdesk vs Zendesk compared for help desk support. We evaluate pricing, ticketing, AI features, and integrations to find your best fit.'
);

-- =============================================
-- E-commerce Comparisons (11-18)
-- =============================================

-- 11. Shopify vs WooCommerce
INSERT INTO comparisons (slug, category_slug, tool_a_id, tool_b_id, intro_content, verdict_content, migration_content, scenario_content, feature_matrix, faqs, meta_title, meta_description)
VALUES (
  'shopify-vs-woocommerce',
  'ecommerce',
  (SELECT id FROM tools WHERE slug='shopify' LIMIT 1),
  (SELECT id FROM tools WHERE slug='woocommerce' LIMIT 1),
  '<p>Shopify and WooCommerce together power the majority of online stores worldwide, representing two fundamentally different approaches to e-commerce. Shopify is a fully hosted platform where everything from servers to security is managed for you. WooCommerce is an open-source WordPress plugin that gives you total control but requires self-hosting and technical management.</p><p>The hosted-versus-open-source debate shapes every aspect of the comparison, from setup time and ongoing maintenance to customization depth and total cost of ownership. Shopify gets you selling in hours, while WooCommerce offers unlimited flexibility for those willing to invest the technical effort.</p><p>We compare both platforms on ease of use, pricing, customization, scalability, and the real-world trade-offs that matter when choosing your store''s foundation.</p>',
  '<p>Choose Shopify if you want a turnkey e-commerce solution that handles hosting, security, updates, and payments so you can focus entirely on selling. Choose WooCommerce if you need full code-level control, want to avoid monthly platform fees, or already run a WordPress site and want to add commerce capabilities.</p><p>Shopify wins on convenience and speed to market. WooCommerce wins on flexibility and long-term cost control.</p>',
  '<p>Both platforms offer migration tools and services. Shopify has a Store Importer app that pulls products, customers, and orders from WooCommerce. Moving from Shopify to WooCommerce requires plugins like Cart2Cart or manual CSV migration. URL redirects and SEO preservation require careful planning regardless of direction. Allow two to six weeks for a thorough migration.</p>',
  '<ul><li><strong>First-time store owner:</strong> Shopify''s guided setup, built-in payments, and app store let non-technical founders launch a professional store within a day.</li><li><strong>Developer building a custom store:</strong> WooCommerce''s open-source codebase, hooks, and REST API allow developers to build exactly what they envision without platform constraints.</li><li><strong>High-volume dropshipping:</strong> Shopify''s native integration with Oberlo and DSers, plus reliable infrastructure, handles high-order-volume dropshipping stores effectively.</li><li><strong>Content-driven commerce (blog + shop):</strong> WooCommerce on WordPress combines best-in-class blogging with commerce, ideal for brands where content drives sales.</li></ul>',
  '[{"feature":"Setup time","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Hours to launch","toolBValue":"Days to weeks","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Monthly platform cost","category":"Pricing","toolAValue":"$39/mo Basic plan","toolBValue":"Free plugin, pay for hosting","winner":"b"},{"feature":"Transaction fees","category":"Pricing","toolAValue":"0% with Shopify Payments","toolBValue":"Payment gateway fees only","winner":"tie"},{"feature":"Customization","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Theme and app based","toolBValue":"Unlimited code-level control","winner":"b"},{"feature":"Hosting management","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Fully managed","toolBValue":"Self-managed or managed WP host","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Plugin/app ecosystem","category":"Integration","toolAValue":"8,000+ apps","toolBValue":"59,000+ WordPress plugins","winner":"b"},{"feature":"SEO capabilities","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Good built-in SEO","toolBValue":"Superior with Yoast/RankMath","winner":"b"},{"feature":"Security and updates","category":"Support","toolAValue":"Automatic, PCI compliant","toolBValue":"Manual updates, self-managed SSL","winner":"a"}]',
  '[{"question":"Which is cheaper in the long run?","answer":"WooCommerce can be cheaper since you avoid monthly platform fees, but hosting, premium plugins, and developer costs add up. Shopify''s predictable monthly pricing often results in comparable total costs for small to mid-size stores."},{"question":"Can WooCommerce handle high traffic like Shopify?","answer":"Yes, with proper hosting. WooCommerce on managed WordPress hosts like Kinsta or WP Engine handles millions of visitors. However, Shopify''s infrastructure requires zero server management for the same scale."},{"question":"Which platform has better payment options?","answer":"Both support all major payment gateways. Shopify Payments (powered by Stripe) simplifies setup with zero additional transaction fees. WooCommerce supports more gateways through plugins but requires individual configuration."}]',
  'Shopify vs WooCommerce (2026): Honest Comparison',
  'Shopify vs WooCommerce compared for e-commerce. We analyze hosting, pricing, customization, and scalability to help you build your online store.'
);

-- 12. Shopify vs BigCommerce
INSERT INTO comparisons (slug, category_slug, tool_a_id, tool_b_id, intro_content, verdict_content, migration_content, scenario_content, feature_matrix, faqs, meta_title, meta_description)
VALUES (
  'shopify-vs-bigcommerce',
  'ecommerce',
  (SELECT id FROM tools WHERE slug='shopify' LIMIT 1),
  (SELECT id FROM tools WHERE slug='bigcommerce' LIMIT 1),
  '<p>Shopify and BigCommerce are the two leading hosted e-commerce platforms, both offering fully managed solutions that let merchants focus on selling rather than server management. While they compete directly, their approaches differ in meaningful ways that affect your store''s capabilities and costs.</p><p>Shopify dominates in market share and app ecosystem, making it the default choice for many merchants. BigCommerce counters with more built-in features out of the box, no transaction fees on any payment gateway, and stronger native B2B capabilities. The choice often comes down to ecosystem size versus feature value.</p><p>We compare both platforms on pricing, built-in features, scalability, and the real costs of running a store on each to help you make an informed decision.</p>',
  '<p>Choose Shopify for its massive app ecosystem, superior theme marketplace, and the largest community of developers and designers. Choose BigCommerce if you want more features included without paid apps, need B2B capabilities, or prefer the freedom to use any payment gateway without extra transaction fees.</p><p>Shopify wins on ecosystem and market presence. BigCommerce wins on built-in value and B2B readiness.</p>',
  '<p>BigCommerce and Shopify both offer migration tools and CSV-based import/export. Third-party services like LitExtension and Cart2Cart automate the process including products, customers, orders, and blog posts. URL structure differences require careful redirect mapping. Plan for two to four weeks for a complete migration with SEO preservation.</p>',
  '<ul><li><strong>Single-brand DTC store:</strong> Shopify''s polished themes, one-click checkout, and Shop app create a seamless direct-to-consumer brand experience.</li><li><strong>B2B wholesale operation:</strong> BigCommerce''s native price lists, customer groups, and quote management support B2B workflows without third-party apps.</li><li><strong>Multi-channel selling:</strong> Shopify''s deep integrations with Instagram, TikTok, Facebook, and Google Shopping make it ideal for social commerce strategies.</li><li><strong>Store with many product variants:</strong> BigCommerce supports 600 SKU variants per product natively, far exceeding Shopify''s 100-variant limit without workarounds.</li></ul>',
  '[{"feature":"Monthly pricing","category":"Pricing","toolAValue":"$39-$399/mo","toolBValue":"$39-$399/mo","winner":"tie"},{"feature":"Transaction fees","category":"Pricing","toolAValue":"0.5-2% on non-Shopify Payments","toolBValue":"No transaction fees ever","winner":"b"},{"feature":"Built-in features","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Basic, extend via apps","toolBValue":"Rich features out of the box","winner":"b"},{"feature":"Theme marketplace","category":"Core","toolAValue":"200+ themes","toolBValue":"Smaller theme selection","winner":"a"},{"feature":"App ecosystem","category":"Integration","toolAValue":"8,000+ apps","toolBValue":"1,200+ apps","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Product variant limit","category":"Core","toolAValue":"100 variants per product","toolBValue":"600 variants per product","winner":"b"},{"feature":"B2B features","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Shopify Plus B2B add-on","toolBValue":"Native B2B Edition included","winner":"b"},{"feature":"Developer community","category":"Support","toolAValue":"Largest e-commerce dev community","toolBValue":"Smaller but growing community","winner":"a"}]',
  '[{"question":"Does BigCommerce charge transaction fees?","answer":"No. BigCommerce never charges transaction fees regardless of which payment gateway you use. Shopify charges 0.5-2% on orders processed through third-party gateways (not Shopify Payments)."},{"question":"Which platform is better for SEO?","answer":"Both offer solid SEO capabilities. BigCommerce provides more SEO features natively, including customizable URLs and automatic 301 redirects. Shopify requires apps for some advanced SEO functions but performs comparably with them."},{"question":"Can I use headless commerce with either platform?","answer":"Yes. Both offer headless commerce APIs. Shopify''s Hydrogen framework and BigCommerce''s Open SaaS approach both support modern headless storefronts with frameworks like Next.js."}]',
  'Shopify vs BigCommerce (2026): Honest Comparison',
  'Shopify vs BigCommerce compared for online stores. We evaluate pricing, transaction fees, features, and scalability for your e-commerce business.'
);

-- 13. Shopify vs Squarespace
INSERT INTO comparisons (slug, category_slug, tool_a_id, tool_b_id, intro_content, verdict_content, migration_content, scenario_content, feature_matrix, faqs, meta_title, meta_description)
VALUES (
  'shopify-vs-squarespace',
  'ecommerce',
  (SELECT id FROM tools WHERE slug='shopify' LIMIT 1),
  (SELECT id FROM tools WHERE slug='squarespace' LIMIT 1),
  '<p>Shopify and Squarespace represent different philosophies in online selling. Shopify is a dedicated e-commerce platform built from the ground up for selling products at scale. Squarespace is a website builder with increasingly capable commerce features, renowned for its stunning design templates and brand-building tools.</p><p>For businesses where visual branding and content are as important as the shopping experience, Squarespace offers an elegant unified solution. For merchants whose primary goal is maximizing sales through advanced e-commerce features, Shopify provides deeper commercial capabilities.</p><p>This comparison examines design quality, e-commerce depth, pricing, and the overall experience of building and running an online store on each platform.</p>',
  '<p>Choose Shopify if selling products is your primary business activity and you need advanced inventory, shipping, and payment features. Choose Squarespace if design excellence and brand presentation are your top priorities, and your commerce needs are straightforward with a smaller product catalog.</p><p>Shopify is the better store. Squarespace is the better website that also sells.</p>',
  '<p>Shopify offers import tools that can bring in products from Squarespace via CSV export. Moving from Shopify to Squarespace involves exporting products and recreating pages in Squarespace''s editor. Design elements won''t transfer between platforms. Allow one to three weeks for migration depending on catalog size and content volume.</p>',
  '<ul><li><strong>Artist or photographer selling prints:</strong> Squarespace''s gallery templates and visual design tools showcase creative work beautifully while enabling sales.</li><li><strong>Growing e-commerce brand with 1,000+ SKUs:</strong> Shopify''s inventory management, variant handling, and fulfillment integrations handle large catalogs efficiently.</li><li><strong>Restaurant or service business with some products:</strong> Squarespace''s scheduling, menu pages, and light commerce features serve service businesses with occasional product sales.</li><li><strong>Dropshipping or print-on-demand business:</strong> Shopify''s integration ecosystem with Printful, Printify, and dropshipping apps far exceeds Squarespace''s limited options.</li></ul>',
  '[{"feature":"Design quality","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Good, template-based","toolBValue":"Award-winning templates","winner":"b"},{"feature":"E-commerce depth","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Advanced commerce features","toolBValue":"Basic to moderate commerce","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Monthly pricing","category":"Pricing","toolAValue":"$39/mo Basic","toolBValue":"$33/mo Commerce Basic","winner":"b"},{"feature":"Product limit","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Unlimited products","toolBValue":"Unlimited products","winner":"tie"},{"feature":"Payment options","category":"Core","toolAValue":"100+ gateways","toolBValue":"Stripe, PayPal, Square","winner":"a"},{"feature":"App ecosystem","category":"Integration","toolAValue":"8,000+ apps","toolBValue":"Limited extensions","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Blogging","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Basic built-in blog","toolBValue":"Excellent built-in blog","winner":"b"},{"feature":"Abandoned cart recovery","category":"Core","toolAValue":"All paid plans","toolBValue":"Commerce plans only","winner":"a"}]',
  '[{"question":"Can Squarespace handle a large online store?","answer":"Squarespace works well for stores with up to a few hundred products. For stores with thousands of SKUs, complex variants, or high order volumes, Shopify''s dedicated e-commerce infrastructure scales more reliably."},{"question":"Which platform has better design templates?","answer":"Squarespace is widely regarded as having the most beautiful website templates available. Shopify''s themes are improving but tend to be more functional than artistic in their default designs."},{"question":"Is Squarespace cheaper than Shopify for small stores?","answer":"Yes. Squarespace''s Commerce Basic plan at $33/month is less expensive than Shopify''s Basic at $39/month, and includes hosting for your entire website, not just the store."}]',
  'Shopify vs Squarespace (2026): Honest Comparison',
  'Shopify vs Squarespace compared for online selling. We evaluate design, e-commerce features, pricing, and ease of use for your store.'
);

-- 14. WooCommerce vs Magento
INSERT INTO comparisons (slug, category_slug, tool_a_id, tool_b_id, intro_content, verdict_content, migration_content, scenario_content, feature_matrix, faqs, meta_title, meta_description)
VALUES (
  'woocommerce-vs-magento',
  'ecommerce',
  (SELECT id FROM tools WHERE slug='woocommerce' LIMIT 1),
  (SELECT id FROM tools WHERE slug='magento' LIMIT 1),
  '<p>WooCommerce and Magento (now Adobe Commerce) are the two dominant open-source e-commerce platforms, each powering hundreds of thousands of online stores. WooCommerce extends WordPress into a capable commerce platform with a gentle learning curve. Magento is a standalone e-commerce powerhouse built for complex, large-scale retail operations.</p><p>The gap between these platforms is primarily one of scale and complexity. WooCommerce handles small to mid-size stores beautifully with minimal technical overhead. Magento excels when you need multi-store management, complex product configurations, advanced B2B features, and enterprise-grade performance.</p><p>We compare both open-source platforms on technical requirements, scalability, feature depth, and total cost of ownership to help you choose the right foundation for your store.</p>',
  '<p>Choose WooCommerce for small to mid-size stores where ease of use, lower development costs, and WordPress integration are priorities. Choose Magento for large-scale operations with complex catalogs, multi-store requirements, B2B commerce needs, or when you need a platform that scales to millions of products and transactions.</p><p>WooCommerce wins on accessibility. Magento wins on enterprise power.</p>',
  '<p>Migration between WooCommerce and Magento requires careful planning due to their different architectures. Tools like LitExtension and Cart2Cart handle product, customer, and order migration. Theme and customization work must be rebuilt from scratch. Magento-to-WooCommerce migrations simplify the tech stack; WooCommerce-to-Magento migrations add capability but increase complexity. Budget four to twelve weeks.</p>',
  '<ul><li><strong>Small boutique with 200 products:</strong> WooCommerce''s simplicity, low hosting costs, and vast plugin ecosystem make it the practical choice for small retailers.</li><li><strong>Multi-brand enterprise with 50K+ SKUs:</strong> Magento''s multi-store architecture, advanced catalog management, and performance optimization handle massive inventories across brands.</li><li><strong>WordPress blogger adding a shop:</strong> WooCommerce installs as a plugin on existing WordPress sites, making it seamless for bloggers to monetize their audience.</li><li><strong>B2B manufacturer with complex pricing:</strong> Magento''s tiered pricing, customer-specific catalogs, quote system, and requisition lists serve B2B commerce natively.</li></ul>',
  '[{"feature":"Setup complexity","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Moderate, WordPress-based","toolBValue":"High, requires developers","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Software cost","category":"Pricing","toolAValue":"Free plugin","toolBValue":"Free Open Source / Paid Commerce","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Hosting cost","category":"Pricing","toolAValue":"$10-100/mo typical","toolBValue":"$50-500/mo typical","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Product limit scalability","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Practical limit ~10K products","toolBValue":"Handles millions of products","winner":"b"},{"feature":"Multi-store support","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Multisite with limitations","toolBValue":"Native multi-store from one admin","winner":"b"},{"feature":"B2B features","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Via plugins","toolBValue":"Comprehensive native B2B","winner":"b"},{"feature":"Developer availability","category":"Support","toolAValue":"Large WordPress dev pool","toolBValue":"Smaller, specialized dev pool","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Extension marketplace","category":"Integration","toolAValue":"59,000+ WP plugins","toolBValue":"4,000+ Magento extensions","winner":"a"}]',
  '[{"question":"Is Magento overkill for small businesses?","answer":"Yes, in most cases. Magento''s complexity, hosting requirements, and development costs make it impractical for stores with fewer than 1,000 products or limited technical resources. WooCommerce or Shopify are better fits."},{"question":"Can WooCommerce scale to enterprise level?","answer":"With proper hosting and optimization, WooCommerce handles stores with tens of thousands of products and significant traffic. However, beyond that scale, Magento''s architecture is purpose-built for enterprise performance."},{"question":"Which platform has lower total cost of ownership?","answer":"WooCommerce has significantly lower TCO for small to mid-size stores due to cheaper hosting, free plugins, and affordable developer rates. Magento''s TCO is higher but justified for enterprise operations where its capabilities prevent revenue loss."}]',
  'WooCommerce vs Magento (2026): Honest Comparison',
  'WooCommerce vs Magento compared for open-source e-commerce. We evaluate scalability, costs, features, and complexity to guide your choice.'
);

-- 15. Wix vs Squarespace
INSERT INTO comparisons (slug, category_slug, tool_a_id, tool_b_id, intro_content, verdict_content, migration_content, scenario_content, feature_matrix, faqs, meta_title, meta_description)
VALUES (
  'wix-vs-squarespace',
  'ecommerce',
  (SELECT id FROM tools WHERE slug='wix' LIMIT 1),
  (SELECT id FROM tools WHERE slug='squarespace' LIMIT 1),
  '<p>Wix and Squarespace are the two most popular website builders for individuals and small businesses, each making it possible to create a professional website without coding skills. Wix offers maximum creative freedom with its drag-and-drop editor. Squarespace provides curated, design-forward templates that ensure every site looks polished.</p><p>The philosophical difference is freedom versus guidance. Wix lets you place any element anywhere on the page, which enables creativity but can lead to inconsistent designs. Squarespace''s structured templates constrain placement but guarantee cohesive, professional results every time.</p><p>We compare both platforms on design flexibility, e-commerce capabilities, pricing, SEO, and overall ease of building and maintaining a website for your business.</p>',
  '<p>Choose Wix if you want maximum design freedom, an AI-powered site builder, and a huge app marketplace for extending functionality. Choose Squarespace if you prioritize design quality, brand consistency, and an elegant all-in-one experience without needing third-party apps.</p><p>Wix wins on flexibility and features. Squarespace wins on design polish and brand presentation.</p>',
  '<p>Neither platform offers a direct migration path to the other. Content must be manually recreated, though text and images can be copied. Third-party tools handle basic content transfer but design work starts from scratch. Squarespace allows limited data export; Wix sites are more locked into their platform. Plan for one to three weeks of rebuilding.</p>',
  '<ul><li><strong>Local service business (plumber, salon):</strong> Wix''s templates, booking system, and local SEO tools help service businesses establish an online presence quickly and affordably.</li><li><strong>Creative professional portfolio:</strong> Squarespace''s gallery layouts and typography create stunning portfolios for photographers, designers, and artists.</li><li><strong>Small restaurant or cafe:</strong> Wix''s restaurant-specific features including online ordering, menus, and reservations serve food businesses comprehensively.</li><li><strong>Fashion or lifestyle brand:</strong> Squarespace''s editorial-style templates and built-in commerce create a cohesive brand experience that resonates with style-conscious audiences.</li></ul>',
  '[{"feature":"Design freedom","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Full drag-and-drop freedom","toolBValue":"Structured template-based","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Template quality","category":"Core","toolAValue":"900+ templates, variable quality","toolBValue":"150+ curated, consistently stunning","winner":"b"},{"feature":"E-commerce pricing","category":"Pricing","toolAValue":"$17/mo Business, $27/mo eCommerce","toolBValue":"$33/mo Commerce Basic","winner":"a"},{"feature":"App marketplace","category":"Integration","toolAValue":"800+ Wix apps","toolBValue":"Limited extensions","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Blogging","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Good blogging features","toolBValue":"Excellent blogging platform","winner":"b"},{"feature":"SEO tools","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Wix SEO Wiz built-in","toolBValue":"Solid SEO fundamentals","winner":"tie"},{"feature":"AI website builder","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Wix ADI creates sites automatically","toolBValue":"No AI builder yet","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Customer support","category":"Support","toolAValue":"Phone, chat, email","toolBValue":"Email and chat, no phone","winner":"a"}]',
  '[{"question":"Which platform is better for e-commerce?","answer":"Both handle basic e-commerce well. Wix offers more affordable commerce plans and a larger app marketplace for store extensions. Squarespace provides more elegant product presentation and built-in features without needing apps."},{"question":"Can I switch my template after building my site?","answer":"Squarespace allows switching templates while preserving content. Wix requires rebuilding the site if you change templates, though its AI builder can help generate a new design quickly."},{"question":"Which platform loads faster?","answer":"Both have improved significantly. Squarespace generally delivers slightly faster load times due to its optimized template system, while Wix''s performance depends on how many apps and custom elements are added."}]',
  'Wix vs Squarespace (2026): Honest Comparison',
  'Wix vs Squarespace compared for website building. We evaluate design, e-commerce, pricing, and ease of use to find your best website platform.'
);

-- 16. Stripe vs PayPal Commerce
INSERT INTO comparisons (slug, category_slug, tool_a_id, tool_b_id, intro_content, verdict_content, migration_content, scenario_content, feature_matrix, faqs, meta_title, meta_description)
VALUES (
  'stripe-vs-paypal-commerce',
  'ecommerce',
  (SELECT id FROM tools WHERE slug='stripe' LIMIT 1),
  (SELECT id FROM tools WHERE slug='paypal-commerce' LIMIT 1),
  '<p>Stripe and PayPal Commerce Platform are the two dominant payment processing solutions for online businesses. Stripe has become the developer''s payment platform of choice, offering elegant APIs and comprehensive financial infrastructure. PayPal Commerce leverages its massive consumer base and trusted brand to offer merchants access to billions of PayPal and Venmo users.</p><p>The decision between these platforms goes beyond transaction fees. Stripe excels at developer experience, subscription billing, and financial tooling. PayPal Commerce offers instant consumer trust, buyer protection, and a checkout flow that millions of shoppers already know and prefer.</p><p>We compare both payment platforms on fees, features, developer experience, checkout conversion, and the overall value they bring to different types of online businesses.</p>',
  '<p>Choose Stripe if you need developer-friendly APIs, advanced subscription billing, or comprehensive financial infrastructure for a platform or marketplace. Choose PayPal Commerce if your customers expect PayPal checkout, you sell internationally where PayPal adoption is high, or you want to accept payments quickly without development work.</p><p>Stripe wins for technical teams and platforms. PayPal wins for consumer trust and global reach.</p>',
  '<p>Switching between Stripe and PayPal Commerce is common since many businesses use both simultaneously. Subscription migrations require re-collecting payment methods from customers. Most platforms and e-commerce solutions support both processors. Plan for one to two weeks to test the new integration and two to four weeks for subscription customer migration.</p>',
  '<ul><li><strong>SaaS company with subscription billing:</strong> Stripe''s Billing product handles complex subscription logic including trials, proration, metered billing, and dunning management natively.</li><li><strong>Small business selling to consumers:</strong> PayPal''s trusted checkout button increases conversion, especially for first-time customers unfamiliar with the merchant''s brand.</li><li><strong>Marketplace platform connecting buyers and sellers:</strong> Stripe Connect provides a comprehensive framework for marketplace payments including splits, payouts, and onboarding.</li><li><strong>International store selling to 200+ countries:</strong> PayPal''s presence in 200+ markets and support for 100+ currencies with localized checkout experiences simplifies global selling.</li></ul>',
  '[{"feature":"Processing fee","category":"Pricing","toolAValue":"2.9% + $0.30 per transaction","toolBValue":"2.99% + $0.49 per transaction","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Developer experience","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Best-in-class APIs and docs","toolBValue":"Adequate APIs, less elegant","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Consumer recognition","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Behind-the-scenes processor","toolBValue":"Globally trusted brand","winner":"b"},{"feature":"Subscription billing","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Advanced Billing product","toolBValue":"Basic recurring payments","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Payout speed","category":"Core","toolAValue":"2 business days standard","toolBValue":"Instant to PayPal balance","winner":"b"},{"feature":"Marketplace support","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Stripe Connect platform","toolBValue":"PayPal for Marketplaces","winner":"a"},{"feature":"No-code options","category":"Integration","toolAValue":"Payment Links, hosted checkout","toolBValue":"PayPal buttons, hosted checkout","winner":"tie"},{"feature":"Chargeback protection","category":"Support","toolAValue":"Radar fraud prevention","toolBValue":"Seller Protection program","winner":"tie"}]',
  '[{"question":"Can I use both Stripe and PayPal together?","answer":"Yes, and most successful e-commerce stores do. Offering both Stripe (for card payments) and PayPal (as an alternative) maximizes checkout conversion by accommodating all customer preferences."},{"question":"Which has lower fees for small businesses?","answer":"Stripe''s per-transaction fee is slightly lower at 2.9% + $0.30 versus PayPal''s 2.99% + $0.49. For a $50 average order, this saves roughly $0.24 per transaction with Stripe."},{"question":"Which is better for international payments?","answer":"PayPal has broader consumer adoption globally, making it preferred for B2C international sales. Stripe supports more currencies and offers better tools for businesses with complex international payment infrastructure needs."}]',
  'Stripe vs PayPal Commerce (2026): Honest Comparison',
  'Stripe vs PayPal Commerce compared for payment processing. Evaluate fees, APIs, checkout conversion, and features to choose your payment stack.'
);

-- 17. Shopify vs Wix
INSERT INTO comparisons (slug, category_slug, tool_a_id, tool_b_id, intro_content, verdict_content, migration_content, scenario_content, feature_matrix, faqs, meta_title, meta_description)
VALUES (
  'shopify-vs-wix',
  'ecommerce',
  (SELECT id FROM tools WHERE slug='shopify' LIMIT 1),
  (SELECT id FROM tools WHERE slug='wix' LIMIT 1),
  '<p>Shopify and Wix eCommerce cater to different merchants with different priorities. Shopify is a purpose-built e-commerce platform designed to power online stores of any size with advanced selling features. Wix is a general-purpose website builder with robust e-commerce capabilities that continue to improve with each update.</p><p>The distinction matters because Shopify thinks commerce-first in every feature decision, from checkout optimization to multi-channel selling to inventory management. Wix thinks website-first, making it ideal when your online store is one part of a broader web presence that includes content, booking, or portfolio elements.</p><p>We compare both platforms on e-commerce features, pricing, design tools, and scalability to help you decide whether you need a store that has a website or a website that has a store.</p>',
  '<p>Choose Shopify when e-commerce is your primary business and you need advanced selling tools like multi-channel commerce, abandoned cart flows, and comprehensive shipping management. Choose Wix when you need a beautiful website that also sells products, and your commerce needs are moderate with fewer than a few hundred products.</p><p>Shopify is the better store platform. Wix is the better website-with-a-store platform.</p>',
  '<p>Shopify accepts product imports via CSV and has third-party migration tools. Wix provides product export in CSV format. Moving from Wix to Shopify is more common as stores grow. Design and content must be rebuilt on the new platform. Budget one to three weeks depending on catalog size and content complexity.</p>',
  '<ul><li><strong>Full-time e-commerce business:</strong> Shopify''s dedicated commerce features, POS system, and multi-channel capabilities support businesses where selling is the core activity.</li><li><strong>Local bakery or food business:</strong> Wix''s combined website builder with ordering, menus, and basic e-commerce serves local food businesses without e-commerce complexity.</li><li><strong>Fashion brand with content focus:</strong> Shopify''s lookbook themes and marketing integrations combine commerce with brand storytelling for fashion retailers.</li><li><strong>Consultant selling digital products:</strong> Wix''s website plus booking plus light digital sales handles consultants who need a web presence with occasional product sales.</li></ul>',
  '[{"feature":"E-commerce depth","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Purpose-built commerce platform","toolBValue":"Website builder with commerce","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Starting price (commerce)","category":"Pricing","toolAValue":"$39/mo Basic Shopify","toolBValue":"$17/mo Business, $27/mo eCommerce","winner":"b"},{"feature":"Design flexibility","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Theme-based customization","toolBValue":"Drag-and-drop total freedom","winner":"b"},{"feature":"Multi-channel selling","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Facebook, Instagram, TikTok, Amazon","toolBValue":"Facebook, Instagram, limited others","winner":"a"},{"feature":"POS system","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Shopify POS included","toolBValue":"No native POS","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Shipping features","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Carrier rates, labels, tracking","toolBValue":"Basic shipping options","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Non-commerce features","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Blog, basic pages","toolBValue":"Booking, events, forums, blog","winner":"b"},{"feature":"App ecosystem","category":"Integration","toolAValue":"8,000+ Shopify apps","toolBValue":"800+ Wix apps","winner":"a"}]',
  '[{"question":"Is Wix eCommerce good enough for a real store?","answer":"Yes, for stores with a moderate product catalog and straightforward shipping needs. Wix eCommerce handles payments, inventory, and order management capably. Larger stores or those needing advanced features will benefit from Shopify."},{"question":"Which platform offers better marketing tools?","answer":"Both include email marketing and SEO tools. Shopify''s marketing ecosystem is deeper with Kit, Shopify Email, and extensive marketing app integrations. Wix includes Ascend for basic marketing within its platform."},{"question":"Can I migrate from Wix to Shopify later?","answer":"Yes. Product catalogs can be exported from Wix and imported into Shopify via CSV. Customer accounts and order history require manual migration or third-party tools. Most stores complete the transition in one to two weeks."}]',
  'Shopify vs Wix (2026): Honest Comparison',
  'Shopify vs Wix compared for online selling. We analyze e-commerce depth, design, pricing, and multi-channel features to help you choose.'
);

-- 18. Gumroad vs Etsy
INSERT INTO comparisons (slug, category_slug, tool_a_id, tool_b_id, intro_content, verdict_content, migration_content, scenario_content, feature_matrix, faqs, meta_title, meta_description)
VALUES (
  'gumroad-vs-etsy',
  'ecommerce',
  (SELECT id FROM tools WHERE slug='gumroad' LIMIT 1),
  (SELECT id FROM tools WHERE slug='etsy' LIMIT 1),
  '<p>Gumroad and Etsy serve creators who want to sell their work online, but they operate as fundamentally different types of platforms. Gumroad is a creator-focused selling tool that lets you sell digital products, subscriptions, and physical goods directly to your audience. Etsy is a marketplace with millions of active shoppers browsing for handmade, vintage, and unique items.</p><p>The marketplace-versus-direct-sales distinction is critical. Etsy brings built-in traffic and discovery, meaning buyers can find your products without you driving traffic. Gumroad requires you to bring your own audience but gives you full control over branding, pricing, and customer relationships.</p><p>This comparison evaluates both platforms on fees, audience access, product types, branding control, and earning potential for different types of creators.</p>',
  '<p>Choose Gumroad if you have an existing audience, sell digital products or memberships, and want full control over your brand and customer relationships. Choose Etsy if you sell physical handmade or vintage goods and want access to a built-in marketplace of millions of active buyers.</p><p>Gumroad wins for digital creators with audiences. Etsy wins for physical product makers seeking marketplace discovery.</p>',
  '<p>Moving between Gumroad and Etsy is straightforward since product listings are simple on both platforms. Digital products transfer easily between them. The main consideration is that Etsy customers and reviews stay on Etsy, while Gumroad customer emails and data stay with you. Many creators sell on both platforms simultaneously to maximize reach.</p>',
  '<ul><li><strong>Course creator or educator:</strong> Gumroad''s digital delivery, licensing, and membership features serve course creators who sell directly to their email list or social following.</li><li><strong>Handmade jewelry maker:</strong> Etsy''s marketplace exposure, category browsing, and buyer trust drive organic sales for handmade physical goods.</li><li><strong>Newsletter writer offering paid content:</strong> Gumroad''s subscription and membership tools integrate with email workflows for writers monetizing their audience.</li><li><strong>Vintage clothing reseller:</strong> Etsy''s vintage category attracts dedicated vintage shoppers who specifically search the platform for curated secondhand finds.</li></ul>',
  '[{"feature":"Platform fee","category":"Pricing","toolAValue":"10% flat fee on sales","toolBValue":"6.5% transaction + 3% + $0.25 payment","winner":"tie"},{"feature":"Monthly fee","category":"Pricing","toolAValue":"No monthly fee","toolBValue":"$0.20 per listing","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Built-in traffic","category":"Core","toolAValue":"No marketplace discovery","toolBValue":"Millions of active shoppers","winner":"b"},{"feature":"Digital products","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Excellent digital delivery","toolBValue":"Basic digital downloads","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Subscriptions/memberships","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Built-in membership tools","toolBValue":"Not available","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Branding control","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Custom pages and branding","toolBValue":"Limited within Etsy framework","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Customer data ownership","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Full customer email access","toolBValue":"Limited buyer communication","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Payment processing","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Included in platform fee","toolBValue":"Etsy Payments required","winner":"tie"}]',
  '[{"question":"Can I sell on both Gumroad and Etsy?","answer":"Absolutely. Many creators maintain an Etsy shop for marketplace discovery and a Gumroad presence for direct sales to their audience. This diversifies revenue streams and reduces platform dependency."},{"question":"Which platform is better for digital products?","answer":"Gumroad is significantly better for digital products with features like license keys, PDF stamping, streaming content, and membership tiers. Etsy supports basic digital downloads but lacks advanced delivery features."},{"question":"Do I need an existing audience for Gumroad?","answer":"Having an audience helps significantly since Gumroad does not provide marketplace traffic. However, Gumroad''s Discover feature and social sharing tools can help new creators gain initial traction."}]',
  'Gumroad vs Etsy (2026): Honest Comparison',
  'Gumroad vs Etsy compared for creators. We evaluate fees, marketplace access, digital products, and branding control for selling your work online.'
);

-- =============================================
-- Marketing Comparisons (19-26)
-- =============================================

-- 19. Mailchimp vs ConvertKit
INSERT INTO comparisons (slug, category_slug, tool_a_id, tool_b_id, intro_content, verdict_content, migration_content, scenario_content, feature_matrix, faqs, meta_title, meta_description)
VALUES (
  'mailchimp-vs-convertkit',
  'marketing',
  (SELECT id FROM tools WHERE slug='mailchimp' LIMIT 1),
  (SELECT id FROM tools WHERE slug='convertkit' LIMIT 1),
  '<p>Mailchimp and ConvertKit represent two distinct approaches to email marketing. Mailchimp has evolved from a simple email tool into a comprehensive marketing platform with landing pages, social ads, and CRM features. ConvertKit stays laser-focused on serving creators, bloggers, and online educators with powerful automation and subscriber management.</p><p>The choice between them often reflects your identity as a business. E-commerce brands and traditional businesses gravitate toward Mailchimp''s visual campaigns and broad marketing suite. Content creators, authors, and course sellers prefer ConvertKit''s subscriber-centric model and clean automation builder.</p><p>We compare both platforms on email design, automation, pricing, deliverability, and how well each serves its target audience to help you invest in the right email platform.</p>',
  '<p>Choose Mailchimp if you need a broad marketing platform with beautiful email templates, e-commerce integrations, and multi-channel capabilities. Choose ConvertKit if you''re a content creator who values powerful automation, subscriber tagging, and a platform built specifically for monetizing an audience.</p><p>Mailchimp wins for visual marketing. ConvertKit wins for creator-focused email strategy.</p>',
  '<p>ConvertKit offers a free concierge migration service for accounts with over 5,000 subscribers, handling the move from Mailchimp including subscriber data, tags, and sequences. Mailchimp accepts CSV imports. The biggest challenge is recreating automation workflows since they don''t transfer directly. Most migrations complete in one to two weeks.</p>',
  '<ul><li><strong>E-commerce store marketing:</strong> Mailchimp''s product recommendations, purchase-triggered emails, and Shopify integration drive repeat sales for online stores.</li><li><strong>Newsletter creator monetizing subscribers:</strong> ConvertKit''s paid newsletter feature, creator profile, and tip jar help writers and educators earn directly from their audience.</li><li><strong>Small business with diverse marketing needs:</strong> Mailchimp''s social posting, ads management, and landing pages provide a unified marketing toolkit beyond just email.</li><li><strong>Blogger building an email course:</strong> ConvertKit''s visual automation builder and sequence editor make it easy to create drip courses that nurture and convert subscribers.</li></ul>',
  '[{"feature":"Free plan","category":"Pricing","toolAValue":"500 contacts, 1,000 sends/mo","toolBValue":"10,000 subscribers, limited sends","winner":"b"},{"feature":"Paid starting price","category":"Pricing","toolAValue":"$13/mo for 500 contacts","toolBValue":"$25/mo for 1,000 subscribers","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Email templates","category":"Core","toolAValue":"100+ visual templates","toolBValue":"Minimal, text-focused designs","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Automation builder","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Visual customer journeys","toolBValue":"Elegant visual automations","winner":"tie"},{"feature":"Subscriber management","category":"Core","toolAValue":"List-based (duplicates possible)","toolBValue":"Tag-based (single subscriber record)","winner":"b"},{"feature":"Landing pages","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Built-in page builder","toolBValue":"Clean landing page builder","winner":"tie"},{"feature":"Creator monetization","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Not available","toolBValue":"Paid newsletters, tip jar","winner":"b"},{"feature":"E-commerce integration","category":"Integration","toolAValue":"Deep Shopify, WooCommerce","toolBValue":"Basic e-commerce connections","winner":"a"}]',
  '[{"question":"Does ConvertKit work well for e-commerce?","answer":"ConvertKit can integrate with Shopify and WooCommerce, but Mailchimp''s e-commerce features are significantly more advanced with product recommendations, purchase tracking, and revenue reporting."},{"question":"Which platform has better email deliverability?","answer":"Both maintain strong deliverability rates. ConvertKit''s text-focused emails often achieve slightly higher inbox placement since they resemble personal emails rather than marketing messages."},{"question":"Can I switch from Mailchimp to ConvertKit easily?","answer":"Yes. ConvertKit offers free migration assistance for larger accounts. Tags, subscriber data, and basic sequences can be transferred. Complex Mailchimp automations and templates need manual recreation."}]',
  'Mailchimp vs ConvertKit (2026): Honest Comparison',
  'Mailchimp vs ConvertKit compared for email marketing. We evaluate automation, pricing, templates, and creator tools to find your ideal platform.'
);

-- 20. Ahrefs vs Semrush
INSERT INTO comparisons (slug, category_slug, tool_a_id, tool_b_id, intro_content, verdict_content, migration_content, scenario_content, feature_matrix, faqs, meta_title, meta_description)
VALUES (
  'ahrefs-vs-semrush',
  'marketing',
  (SELECT id FROM tools WHERE slug='ahrefs' LIMIT 1),
  (SELECT id FROM tools WHERE slug='semrush' LIMIT 1),
  '<p>Ahrefs and Semrush are the two most powerful all-in-one SEO platforms, relied upon by agencies, in-house teams, and independent marketers worldwide. Both provide keyword research, backlink analysis, site auditing, rank tracking, and competitive intelligence, yet each has distinct strengths that matter for different workflows.</p><p>Ahrefs is renowned for its backlink database, content explorer, and clean interface that SEO professionals find efficient for daily research. Semrush offers the broadest digital marketing toolkit, extending beyond SEO into PPC, social media, content marketing, and PR monitoring.</p><p>We compare these SEO powerhouses on data accuracy, feature breadth, pricing, and real-world usability to help you choose the tool that maximizes your marketing ROI.</p>',
  '<p>Choose Ahrefs if backlink analysis, content research, and a focused SEO workflow are your primary needs. Its data quality and interface efficiency make it a favorite among dedicated SEO professionals. Choose Semrush if you want a broader digital marketing suite that covers SEO, PPC, social, and content marketing in one subscription.</p><p>Ahrefs wins for pure SEO depth. Semrush wins for marketing breadth.</p>',
  '<p>Switching between Ahrefs and Semrush involves exporting projects, tracked keywords, and historical data via CSV where supported. Neither platform offers a direct migration tool. Tracked keyword lists and competitor targets need manual setup on the new platform. Most teams run both tools in parallel for a month during transition to ensure data continuity.</p>',
  '<ul><li><strong>Link building campaign:</strong> Ahrefs'' backlink database, broken link finder, and link intersect tool provide the deepest insight for link acquisition strategies.</li><li><strong>Full-service digital agency:</strong> Semrush''s PPC toolkit, social media scheduler, and client reporting serve agencies managing diverse marketing channels for clients.</li><li><strong>Content marketing team:</strong> Ahrefs'' Content Explorer finds top-performing content by topic, while its keyword difficulty scores help prioritize content creation opportunities.</li><li><strong>PPC and SEO combined strategy:</strong> Semrush''s unified keyword database showing organic and paid metrics helps teams coordinate SEO and Google Ads efforts.</li></ul>',
  '[{"feature":"Monthly pricing","category":"Pricing","toolAValue":"$129/mo Lite","toolBValue":"$139.95/mo Pro","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Backlink database","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Largest backlink index","toolBValue":"Comprehensive but smaller","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Keyword database","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Large keyword database","toolBValue":"Largest keyword database","winner":"b"},{"feature":"PPC tools","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Limited PPC features","toolBValue":"Full PPC keyword and ad tools","winner":"b"},{"feature":"Site audit","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Clean, actionable audit","toolBValue":"Detailed with 140+ checks","winner":"b"},{"feature":"Content marketing tools","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Content Explorer","toolBValue":"Content Marketing Toolkit","winner":"tie"},{"feature":"Social media tools","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Not available","toolBValue":"Social posting and analytics","winner":"b"},{"feature":"Interface usability","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Clean, efficient design","toolBValue":"Feature-rich, steeper learning curve","winner":"a"}]',
  '[{"question":"Can I use both Ahrefs and Semrush?","answer":"Many agencies do. Ahrefs is often used for backlink research and content analysis while Semrush handles PPC, reporting, and social media. However, for most teams, one tool covers the vast majority of needs."},{"question":"Which tool has more accurate keyword data?","answer":"Both provide reliable estimates, but neither matches exact Google data. Semrush''s keyword database is larger, while Ahrefs'' keyword difficulty metric is often considered more accurate for predicting ranking difficulty."},{"question":"Is there a free alternative that''s good enough?","answer":"Google Search Console and Google Keyword Planner provide basic keyword and performance data for free. However, they lack the competitive intelligence, backlink analysis, and scale that make Ahrefs and Semrush essential for serious SEO."}]',
  'Ahrefs vs Semrush (2026): Honest Comparison',
  'Ahrefs vs Semrush compared for SEO professionals. We evaluate backlink data, keyword tools, pricing, and feature breadth in this detailed guide.'
);

-- 21. Hootsuite vs Buffer
INSERT INTO comparisons (slug, category_slug, tool_a_id, tool_b_id, intro_content, verdict_content, migration_content, scenario_content, feature_matrix, faqs, meta_title, meta_description)
VALUES (
  'hootsuite-vs-buffer',
  'marketing',
  (SELECT id FROM tools WHERE slug='hootsuite' LIMIT 1),
  (SELECT id FROM tools WHERE slug='buffer' LIMIT 1),
  '<p>Hootsuite and Buffer are two of the longest-standing social media management platforms, helping businesses schedule posts, analyze performance, and manage their social presence. Hootsuite has grown into a comprehensive enterprise social media suite with advanced analytics, social listening, and team collaboration. Buffer has stayed focused on simplicity, offering an intuitive scheduling and analytics experience.</p><p>The platforms have diverged significantly over the years. Hootsuite targets mid-market and enterprise teams that need depth across social media operations. Buffer serves small businesses, creators, and lean marketing teams that value straightforward scheduling without complexity.</p><p>We compare both platforms on scheduling, analytics, pricing, team features, and overall ease of managing a multi-channel social media strategy.</p>',
  '<p>Choose Hootsuite if you manage social media for a large organization and need social listening, advanced analytics, ad management, and team workflows. Choose Buffer if you want a clean, affordable scheduling tool that handles the essentials well without overwhelming your team with features they won''t use.</p><p>Hootsuite wins on enterprise features. Buffer wins on simplicity and value for small teams.</p>',
  '<p>Switching between Hootsuite and Buffer mainly involves reconnecting social accounts and rescheduling queued content. Scheduled posts don''t transfer between platforms. Analytics history stays with the original platform. The migration is technically simple since both connect to the same social APIs, but re-establishing content queues takes time. Allow one to two weeks.</p>',
  '<ul><li><strong>Solo entrepreneur or freelancer:</strong> Buffer''s free plan and intuitive interface let individuals manage three social channels without any cost or learning curve.</li><li><strong>Enterprise brand with 10+ social accounts:</strong> Hootsuite''s bulk scheduling, approval workflows, and social listening handle complex enterprise social media operations.</li><li><strong>Small agency managing multiple clients:</strong> Buffer''s affordable per-channel pricing and clean reporting make it cost-effective for small agencies with straightforward client needs.</li><li><strong>Brand monitoring and reputation management:</strong> Hootsuite''s social listening and streams let brands track mentions, sentiment, and competitor activity in real time.</li></ul>',
  '[{"feature":"Free plan","category":"Pricing","toolAValue":"No free plan","toolBValue":"3 channels, 10 posts/channel","winner":"b"},{"feature":"Starting paid price","category":"Pricing","toolAValue":"$99/mo Professional","toolBValue":"$6/mo per channel","winner":"b"},{"feature":"Social listening","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Built-in listening tools","toolBValue":"Not available","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Content scheduling","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Advanced bulk scheduling","toolBValue":"Clean, intuitive scheduler","winner":"tie"},{"feature":"Analytics depth","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Advanced custom reports","toolBValue":"Clear, essential metrics","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Team collaboration","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Approval workflows, roles","toolBValue":"Basic team features","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Supported platforms","category":"Integration","toolAValue":"All major social networks","toolBValue":"All major social networks","winner":"tie"},{"feature":"Ease of use","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Complex, steeper learning curve","toolBValue":"Extremely intuitive interface","winner":"b"}]',
  '[{"question":"Is Buffer good enough for businesses?","answer":"Yes, for small to mid-size businesses with straightforward social media needs. Buffer handles scheduling, analytics, and basic engagement well. Larger organizations with complex workflows will benefit from Hootsuite''s depth."},{"question":"Why is Hootsuite so much more expensive?","answer":"Hootsuite includes enterprise features like social listening, team approval workflows, ad management, and advanced analytics that Buffer doesn''t offer. You''re paying for a comprehensive social media operating system."},{"question":"Can I manage TikTok with both tools?","answer":"Yes. Both Hootsuite and Buffer support TikTok scheduling and analytics, along with other major platforms like Instagram, Facebook, X (Twitter), LinkedIn, and Pinterest."}]',
  'Hootsuite vs Buffer (2026): Honest Comparison',
  'Hootsuite vs Buffer compared for social media management. We evaluate scheduling, analytics, pricing, and team tools to find your best fit.'
);

-- 22. Mailchimp vs Brevo
INSERT INTO comparisons (slug, category_slug, tool_a_id, tool_b_id, intro_content, verdict_content, migration_content, scenario_content, feature_matrix, faqs, meta_title, meta_description)
VALUES (
  'mailchimp-vs-brevo',
  'marketing',
  (SELECT id FROM tools WHERE slug='mailchimp' LIMIT 1),
  (SELECT id FROM tools WHERE slug='brevo' LIMIT 1),
  '<p>Mailchimp and Brevo (formerly Sendinblue) are popular email marketing platforms that have expanded into broader marketing suites. Mailchimp is the more established name with a massive user base and comprehensive marketing features. Brevo has emerged as a compelling alternative with competitive pricing and a unique email-send-based model rather than subscriber-based pricing.</p><p>The pricing model difference is the most significant factor for many businesses. Mailchimp charges based on subscriber count, meaning costs rise as your list grows regardless of how often you email. Brevo charges based on emails sent, allowing unlimited contacts on every plan including the free tier.</p><p>We compare these platforms on email features, automation, pricing structure, deliverability, and the additional marketing tools each offers beyond email.</p>',
  '<p>Choose Mailchimp if you need a mature marketing platform with extensive templates, deep e-commerce integration, and a comprehensive set of marketing tools beyond email. Choose Brevo if you want affordable email marketing with unlimited contacts, transactional email support, and SMS marketing included in one platform.</p><p>Mailchimp wins on brand recognition and feature maturity. Brevo wins decisively on pricing and value.</p>',
  '<p>Brevo offers import tools that accept Mailchimp CSV exports, bringing over contacts, lists, and basic segmentation. Email templates need to be recreated or imported as HTML. Automation workflows require manual rebuilding. Brevo''s support team assists with migration for larger accounts. Most teams complete the switch in one to two weeks.</p>',
  '<ul><li><strong>Growing business watching costs:</strong> Brevo''s unlimited contacts and send-based pricing keep costs predictable as your email list expands.</li><li><strong>E-commerce brand with Shopify integration:</strong> Mailchimp''s deep Shopify and WooCommerce integrations with product recommendations and purchase tracking serve online retailers effectively.</li><li><strong>Business needing transactional and marketing email:</strong> Brevo handles both marketing campaigns and transactional emails (order confirmations, password resets) from one platform with shared deliverability infrastructure.</li><li><strong>Multi-channel marketer (email + SMS):</strong> Brevo''s built-in SMS marketing alongside email lets businesses coordinate campaigns across channels without additional tools.</li></ul>',
  '[{"feature":"Free plan contacts","category":"Pricing","toolAValue":"500 contacts","toolBValue":"Unlimited contacts","winner":"b"},{"feature":"Free plan sends","category":"Pricing","toolAValue":"1,000 emails/mo","toolBValue":"300 emails/day (9,000/mo)","winner":"b"},{"feature":"Pricing model","category":"Pricing","toolAValue":"Per subscriber","toolBValue":"Per email sent","winner":"b"},{"feature":"Email templates","category":"Core","toolAValue":"100+ polished templates","toolBValue":"60+ modern templates","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Automation","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Advanced customer journeys","toolBValue":"Solid workflow automation","winner":"a"},{"feature":"SMS marketing","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Via add-on only","toolBValue":"Built-in SMS marketing","winner":"b"},{"feature":"Transactional email","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Via Mandrill add-on","toolBValue":"Built-in transactional email","winner":"b"},{"feature":"CRM features","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Basic audience CRM","toolBValue":"Sales CRM with pipeline","winner":"b"}]',
  '[{"question":"Is Brevo as reliable as Mailchimp for deliverability?","answer":"Yes. Brevo maintains strong deliverability rates comparable to Mailchimp. Both platforms offer dedicated IP options and authentication protocols. Deliverability depends more on your sending practices than the platform."},{"question":"Why did Sendinblue rebrand to Brevo?","answer":"Sendinblue rebranded to Brevo in 2023 to reflect its evolution from an email-only tool to a comprehensive CRM and marketing platform that includes email, SMS, chat, and sales features."},{"question":"Which platform is better for large email lists?","answer":"Brevo is significantly more cost-effective for large lists because it charges per email sent, not per subscriber. A business with 100,000 contacts pays dramatically less on Brevo than on Mailchimp."}]',
  'Mailchimp vs Brevo (2026): Honest Comparison',
  'Mailchimp vs Brevo compared for email marketing. We evaluate pricing models, automation, SMS features, and deliverability in this detailed guide.'
);

-- 23. ActiveCampaign vs Mailchimp
INSERT INTO comparisons (slug, category_slug, tool_a_id, tool_b_id, intro_content, verdict_content, migration_content, scenario_content, feature_matrix, faqs, meta_title, meta_description)
VALUES (
  'activecampaign-vs-mailchimp',
  'marketing',
  (SELECT id FROM tools WHERE slug='activecampaign' LIMIT 1),
  (SELECT id FROM tools WHERE slug='mailchimp' LIMIT 1),
  '<p>ActiveCampaign and Mailchimp both help businesses communicate with their audience through email, but they serve different stages of marketing sophistication. Mailchimp is the accessible, all-in-one marketing platform that millions of small businesses start with. ActiveCampaign is the automation-first platform that serious marketers graduate to when they need advanced segmentation and behavioral targeting.</p><p>Where Mailchimp excels at simplicity and breadth, ActiveCampaign dominates in automation depth and CRM integration. ActiveCampaign''s visual automation builder can model complex customer journeys with conditional logic, lead scoring, and multi-channel triggers that Mailchimp simply cannot match.</p><p>We compare both platforms on automation power, ease of use, pricing, CRM features, and the overall sophistication of marketing campaigns each enables.</p>',
  '<p>Choose Mailchimp if you''re a small business or startup that wants an easy-to-use marketing platform with email, ads, and landing pages in one place. Choose ActiveCampaign if you need advanced marketing automation, lead scoring, CRM functionality, and sophisticated customer journey mapping.</p><p>Mailchimp is the easier starting point. ActiveCampaign is the more powerful long-term investment.</p>',
  '<p>ActiveCampaign offers a free migration service that handles contact imports, recreates key automations, and sets up forms from Mailchimp. Their team assists with list restructuring from Mailchimp''s list-based model to ActiveCampaign''s tag-based system. Budget one to three weeks depending on the complexity of existing automations and list size.</p>',
  '<ul><li><strong>E-commerce retention marketing:</strong> ActiveCampaign''s deep WooCommerce and Shopify integrations with behavioral triggers drive sophisticated abandoned cart, win-back, and upsell automations.</li><li><strong>Small business just starting email:</strong> Mailchimp''s free plan and intuitive interface let new businesses send their first campaigns within minutes without technical knowledge.</li><li><strong>B2B company with long sales cycles:</strong> ActiveCampaign''s built-in CRM, lead scoring, and deal pipeline automate nurture sequences that move prospects through complex B2B buying journeys.</li><li><strong>Non-profit sending newsletters:</strong> Mailchimp''s free plan and simple campaign builder serve non-profits with basic email needs without budget strain.</li></ul>',
  '[{"feature":"Automation depth","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Industry-leading visual automations","toolBValue":"Basic customer journeys","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Free plan","category":"Pricing","toolAValue":"14-day trial only","toolBValue":"500 contacts, 1,000 sends","winner":"b"},{"feature":"Starting paid price","category":"Pricing","toolAValue":"$29/mo for 1,000 contacts","toolBValue":"$13/mo for 500 contacts","winner":"b"},{"feature":"Built-in CRM","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Full sales CRM with pipelines","toolBValue":"Basic audience management","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Lead scoring","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Advanced contact and deal scoring","toolBValue":"Not available natively","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Email templates","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Good selection of templates","toolBValue":"Extensive template library","winner":"b"},{"feature":"Conditional content","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Advanced dynamic content","toolBValue":"Basic merge tags","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Site tracking","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Website visit tracking built-in","toolBValue":"Limited page tracking","winner":"a"}]',
  '[{"question":"Is ActiveCampaign worth the higher price?","answer":"For businesses that leverage automation and CRM features, ActiveCampaign''s ROI typically exceeds the price difference. If you only send basic newsletters, Mailchimp''s lower cost makes more sense."},{"question":"Can ActiveCampaign replace both Mailchimp and a CRM?","answer":"Yes. ActiveCampaign''s built-in CRM with deal pipelines, lead scoring, and task management eliminates the need for a separate CRM tool for many small to mid-size businesses."},{"question":"Which platform has better deliverability?","answer":"Both maintain excellent deliverability rates above 95%. ActiveCampaign''s dedicated IP option and predictive sending feature can provide a slight edge for high-volume senders."}]',
  'ActiveCampaign vs Mailchimp (2026): Honest Comparison',
  'ActiveCampaign vs Mailchimp compared for email marketing. Analyze automation, CRM, pricing, and features to choose the right marketing platform.'
);

-- 24. Surfer SEO vs Semrush
INSERT INTO comparisons (slug, category_slug, tool_a_id, tool_b_id, intro_content, verdict_content, migration_content, scenario_content, feature_matrix, faqs, meta_title, meta_description)
VALUES (
  'surfer-seo-vs-semrush',
  'marketing',
  (SELECT id FROM tools WHERE slug='surfer-seo' LIMIT 1),
  (SELECT id FROM tools WHERE slug='semrush' LIMIT 1),
  '<p>Surfer SEO and Semrush serve different facets of the SEO workflow, though they increasingly overlap. Surfer SEO specializes in on-page content optimization, using NLP and SERP analysis to guide writers in creating content that ranks. Semrush is a comprehensive digital marketing suite covering keyword research, backlinks, technical SEO, PPC, and content marketing.</p><p>Many SEO professionals use both tools because they excel at different tasks. Surfer provides unmatched content optimization guidance with real-time scoring and AI writing assistance. Semrush delivers the broader strategic toolkit for keyword research, competitive analysis, and site auditing.</p><p>We compare these platforms on their overlapping and unique capabilities to help you decide whether you need one, the other, or both in your SEO stack.</p>',
  '<p>Choose Surfer SEO if content optimization is your primary need and you want data-driven guidance for creating high-ranking articles. Choose Semrush if you need a comprehensive SEO and digital marketing toolkit that covers keyword research, backlinks, technical audits, and PPC alongside content tools.</p><p>Surfer SEO is the content optimization specialist. Semrush is the full-service marketing command center.</p>',
  '<p>Since Surfer SEO and Semrush serve different primary functions, switching between them isn''t a direct migration. Teams moving from Semrush to Surfer typically keep Semrush for research and add Surfer for content. Moving from Surfer to Semrush''s content tools means accessing a broader toolkit but losing Surfer''s specialized optimization scoring. Most teams transition workflows within a week.</p>',
  '<ul><li><strong>Content writing team producing articles:</strong> Surfer''s content editor with real-time optimization scoring and NLP-based keyword suggestions helps writers create ranking content without SEO expertise.</li><li><strong>SEO agency managing full-service clients:</strong> Semrush''s reporting, keyword tracking, site audits, and backlink tools cover the complete agency SEO workflow for client accounts.</li><li><strong>Blog scaling content production with AI:</strong> Surfer''s AI writing feature combined with its optimization framework accelerates content production while maintaining quality signals.</li><li><strong>PPC and SEO combined strategy:</strong> Semrush''s unified keyword database for organic and paid search helps coordinate SEO and advertising efforts from one platform.</li></ul>',
  '[{"feature":"Content optimization","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Best-in-class content editor","toolBValue":"SEO Writing Assistant","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Keyword research","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Basic keyword suggestions","toolBValue":"Comprehensive keyword toolkit","winner":"b"},{"feature":"Backlink analysis","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Not available","toolBValue":"Full backlink database","winner":"b"},{"feature":"Site audit","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Content audit only","toolBValue":"Comprehensive technical audit","winner":"b"},{"feature":"Monthly pricing","category":"Pricing","toolAValue":"$89/mo Essential","toolBValue":"$139.95/mo Pro","winner":"a"},{"feature":"AI writing","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Surfer AI built-in","toolBValue":"ContentShake AI tool","winner":"a"},{"feature":"SERP analysis","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Deep SERP analyzer","toolBValue":"SERP feature tracking","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Rank tracking","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Not available natively","toolBValue":"Daily rank tracking","winner":"b"}]',
  '[{"question":"Do I need both Surfer SEO and Semrush?","answer":"If content creation is a major part of your SEO strategy, using both is common and effective. Semrush handles research and technical SEO while Surfer optimizes the actual content. For budget-conscious teams, Semrush alone covers more ground."},{"question":"Can Surfer SEO replace Semrush?","answer":"No. Surfer excels at content optimization but lacks keyword research depth, backlink analysis, technical auditing, and PPC tools that Semrush provides. They serve different parts of the SEO workflow."},{"question":"Which tool is better for content briefs?","answer":"Surfer SEO is significantly better for content briefs with its Content Planner creating topical maps and its Editor providing detailed writing guidelines based on SERP analysis."}]',
  'Surfer SEO vs Semrush (2026): Honest Comparison',
  'Surfer SEO vs Semrush compared for SEO workflows. We evaluate content optimization, keyword tools, pricing, and features in this detailed guide.'
);

-- 25. Unbounce vs Leadpages
INSERT INTO comparisons (slug, category_slug, tool_a_id, tool_b_id, intro_content, verdict_content, migration_content, scenario_content, feature_matrix, faqs, meta_title, meta_description)
VALUES (
  'unbounce-vs-leadpages',
  'marketing',
  (SELECT id FROM tools WHERE slug='unbounce' LIMIT 1),
  (SELECT id FROM tools WHERE slug='leadpages' LIMIT 1),
  '<p>Unbounce and Leadpages are dedicated landing page builders that help marketers create high-converting pages without developer assistance. Unbounce pioneered the landing page category and has evolved into an AI-powered conversion platform. Leadpages focuses on affordability and ease of use, making professional landing pages accessible to small businesses.</p><p>Both platforms offer drag-and-drop builders, A/B testing, and conversion optimization, but they target different segments. Unbounce serves mid-market companies and agencies willing to invest more for advanced optimization features. Leadpages attracts small businesses and solopreneurs who need effective pages at a lower price point.</p><p>We compare these platforms on builder quality, conversion features, pricing, and the overall return on investment each delivers for different business sizes.</p>',
  '<p>Choose Unbounce if you run high-volume campaigns, need AI-powered optimization like Smart Traffic, and want the most advanced A/B testing and dynamic text replacement capabilities. Choose Leadpages if you need an affordable landing page solution with solid templates and unlimited page publishing on every plan.</p><p>Unbounce wins on optimization sophistication. Leadpages wins on value and accessibility.</p>',
  '<p>Neither platform offers a direct migration tool. Landing page designs must be recreated on the new platform, though content can be copied. Custom domains need to be reconfigured. Integrations with email tools and CRMs require reconnection. Most teams rebuild their top-performing pages first and complete the migration over two to four weeks.</p>',
  '<ul><li><strong>PPC agency managing client campaigns:</strong> Unbounce''s Smart Traffic, dynamic text replacement, and multi-client management handle agency-scale campaign optimization effectively.</li><li><strong>Small business building a lead funnel:</strong> Leadpages'' affordable pricing, unlimited pages, and built-in lead collection forms serve small businesses building their first conversion funnels.</li><li><strong>SaaS company A/B testing aggressively:</strong> Unbounce''s sophisticated A/B testing with statistical significance and AI optimization accelerate conversion rate improvement for SaaS landing pages.</li><li><strong>Coach or consultant collecting leads:</strong> Leadpages'' templates with built-in checkout and lead magnet delivery help consultants build their practice without technical complexity.</li></ul>',
  '[{"feature":"Monthly pricing","category":"Pricing","toolAValue":"$99/mo Build plan","toolBValue":"$49/mo Standard plan","winner":"b"},{"feature":"Landing page limit","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Tiered by plan","toolBValue":"Unlimited on all plans","winner":"b"},{"feature":"AI optimization","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Smart Traffic AI routing","toolBValue":"Not available","winner":"a"},{"feature":"A/B testing","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Advanced split testing","toolBValue":"Basic A/B testing","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Dynamic text replacement","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Full DTR support","toolBValue":"Not available","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Template quality","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Professional, conversion-focused","toolBValue":"Good templates, growing library","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Builder flexibility","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Pixel-perfect drag and drop","toolBValue":"Section-based builder","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Built-in payments","category":"Integration","toolAValue":"Not native","toolBValue":"Stripe checkout built-in","winner":"b"}]',
  '[{"question":"Is Unbounce worth 2x the price of Leadpages?","answer":"For businesses running high-volume PPC campaigns, Unbounce''s Smart Traffic and advanced optimization features can generate enough additional conversions to justify the price difference through improved ROI."},{"question":"Can Leadpages replace a full website?","answer":"Leadpages includes a basic website builder alongside landing pages, making it possible to run a simple web presence. However, it''s not a replacement for a full website platform like WordPress or Squarespace."},{"question":"Which tool integrates better with email marketing?","answer":"Both integrate with all major email platforms. Unbounce offers more webhook customization and CRM integrations. Leadpages provides simpler, direct integrations that work well for standard email capture workflows."}]',
  'Unbounce vs Leadpages (2026): Honest Comparison',
  'Unbounce vs Leadpages compared for landing pages. We evaluate builders, AI optimization, A/B testing, and pricing to help you convert more leads.'
);

-- 26. Moz vs Ahrefs
INSERT INTO comparisons (slug, category_slug, tool_a_id, tool_b_id, intro_content, verdict_content, migration_content, scenario_content, feature_matrix, faqs, meta_title, meta_description)
VALUES (
  'moz-vs-ahrefs',
  'marketing',
  (SELECT id FROM tools WHERE slug='moz' LIMIT 1),
  (SELECT id FROM tools WHERE slug='ahrefs' LIMIT 1),
  '<p>Moz and Ahrefs are established SEO platforms trusted by thousands of marketers, each with distinct strengths. Moz is one of the original SEO tools, beloved for its educational community, Domain Authority metric, and beginner-friendly interface. Ahrefs has risen to prominence with its massive backlink database, powerful content explorer, and data-rich approach to SEO research.</p><p>The platforms reflect different SEO philosophies. Moz makes SEO accessible with clear metrics and guided recommendations. Ahrefs gives power users raw data and research capabilities that enable deep competitive analysis and content strategy development.</p><p>We compare both tools on data quality, feature sets, pricing, usability, and the unique value each brings to different types of SEO practitioners.</p>',
  '<p>Choose Moz if you''re building an SEO practice and value educational resources, local SEO features, and an approachable interface that helps your team learn. Choose Ahrefs if you need the deepest backlink data, most powerful content research tools, and a platform built for experienced SEO professionals.</p><p>Moz wins for learning and local SEO. Ahrefs wins for data depth and professional research.</p>',
  '<p>Transitioning between Moz and Ahrefs involves recreating tracked campaigns, keyword lists, and competitor targets manually. Neither offers import from the other. Historical data remains in the original platform. Running both in parallel for a month helps validate data consistency. The switch typically takes one to two weeks for setup and team training.</p>',
  '<ul><li><strong>SEO beginner building skills:</strong> Moz''s clear interface, Moz Academy courses, and vibrant community help newcomers learn SEO while practicing with professional tools.</li><li><strong>Local business SEO:</strong> Moz Local''s listing management, review monitoring, and local rank tracking provide a focused local SEO solution that Ahrefs doesn''t offer.</li><li><strong>Content strategist planning topics:</strong> Ahrefs'' Content Explorer surfaces top-performing content by topic with traffic estimates, helping strategists identify proven content opportunities.</li><li><strong>Link building specialist:</strong> Ahrefs'' backlink database, link intersect tool, and broken link finder provide the richest dataset for professional link building campaigns.</li></ul>',
  '[{"feature":"Monthly pricing","category":"Pricing","toolAValue":"$99/mo Standard","toolBValue":"$129/mo Lite","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Backlink database","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Large link index","toolBValue":"Largest backlink database","winner":"b"},{"feature":"Domain Authority metric","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Industry-standard DA/PA","toolBValue":"Domain Rating (DR)","winner":"tie"},{"feature":"Local SEO tools","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Moz Local product","toolBValue":"Limited local features","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Content research","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Basic content analysis","toolBValue":"Powerful Content Explorer","winner":"b"},{"feature":"Keyword research","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Keyword Explorer with priority","toolBValue":"Keywords Explorer with clicks data","winner":"b"},{"feature":"Educational resources","category":"Support","toolAValue":"Moz Academy, blog, community","toolBValue":"Ahrefs Academy and blog","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Site audit","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Solid site crawler","toolBValue":"Fast, detailed site audit","winner":"b"}]',
  '[{"question":"Is Moz still relevant compared to Ahrefs?","answer":"Yes. Moz remains valuable especially for local SEO, beginner-friendly features, and its Domain Authority metric which is still widely used in the industry. However, for advanced research, Ahrefs offers more depth."},{"question":"Which tool updates its data more frequently?","answer":"Ahrefs crawls the web continuously and updates its backlink index daily. Moz updates its link data less frequently but has improved its crawl frequency significantly in recent years."},{"question":"Can I use the free versions of both tools?","answer":"Moz offers a limited free tier and Ahrefs provides free webmaster tools for verified site owners. Both give useful data but with significant restrictions compared to paid plans."}]',
  'Moz vs Ahrefs (2026): Honest Comparison',
  'Moz vs Ahrefs compared for SEO tools. We evaluate backlink data, local SEO, keyword research, and pricing to help you choose the right platform.'
);

