-- 39. ChatGPT vs Gemini
INSERT INTO comparisons (slug, category_slug, tool_a_id, tool_b_id, intro_content, verdict_content, migration_content, scenario_content, feature_matrix, faqs, meta_title, meta_description)
VALUES (
  'chatgpt-vs-gemini',
  'ai-tools',
  (SELECT id FROM tools WHERE slug='chatgpt' LIMIT 1),
  (SELECT id FROM tools WHERE slug='gemini' LIMIT 1),
  '<p>ChatGPT and Gemini are the two most prominent AI assistants reshaping how people work, learn, and create. ChatGPT from OpenAI launched the generative AI revolution and maintains a massive user base with GPT-4 powering its premium tier. Gemini from Google leverages deep integration with Google''s ecosystem including Search, Workspace, and Android.</p><p>Both AI assistants handle writing, coding, analysis, and creative tasks, but their strengths diverge based on their parent companies'' expertise. ChatGPT excels at nuanced conversation, creative writing, and coding assistance. Gemini leverages real-time web access, Google Search integration, and multimodal capabilities across Google''s product suite.</p><p>We compare these AI assistants on response quality, features, pricing, integrations, and the practical value each delivers in daily workflows.</p>',
  '<p>Choose ChatGPT if you need the most capable conversational AI with strong creative writing, coding assistance, and a vast plugin ecosystem. Choose Gemini if you''re embedded in Google''s ecosystem and want AI that integrates directly with Gmail, Docs, Search, and Android.</p><p>ChatGPT wins on conversation quality and plugin ecosystem. Gemini wins on Google integration and real-time information.</p>',
  '<p>There is no data migration between AI assistants since they don''t store persistent user data in comparable ways. Switching is as simple as using a different tool. Chat histories stay in their respective platforms. Custom GPTs in ChatGPT have no Gemini equivalent yet. Most users benefit from having access to both and using each for its strengths.</p>',
  '<ul><li><strong>Content writer drafting articles:</strong> ChatGPT''s creative writing capabilities and tone control produce polished drafts that require less editing than Gemini''s outputs.</li><li><strong>Researcher needing current information:</strong> Gemini''s native Google Search integration provides up-to-date information and source citations for research queries.</li><li><strong>Developer debugging code:</strong> ChatGPT''s code interpreter and strong coding performance across multiple languages make it the preferred AI coding assistant.</li><li><strong>Google Workspace power user:</strong> Gemini''s integration with Gmail, Docs, Sheets, and Slides lets you use AI assistance without leaving Google''s productivity suite.</li></ul>',
  '[{"feature":"Free tier","category":"Pricing","toolAValue":"GPT-4o mini, limited GPT-4o","toolBValue":"Gemini 1.5 Flash, limited Pro","winner":"tie"},{"feature":"Premium pricing","category":"Pricing","toolAValue":"$20/mo ChatGPT Plus","toolBValue":"$20/mo Gemini Advanced","winner":"tie"},{"feature":"Creative writing","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Excellent, nuanced output","toolBValue":"Good, sometimes generic","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Real-time information","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Web browsing available","toolBValue":"Native Google Search","winner":"b"},{"feature":"Coding assistance","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Strong across languages","toolBValue":"Good, improving rapidly","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Multimodal (images)","category":"Core","toolAValue":"DALL-E image generation","toolBValue":"Imagen image generation","winner":"tie"},{"feature":"Ecosystem integration","category":"Integration","toolAValue":"Plugins, GPT Store, API","toolBValue":"Deep Google Workspace integration","winner":"b"},{"feature":"Mobile experience","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Dedicated iOS/Android app","toolBValue":"Built into Android, iOS app","winner":"b"}]',
  '[{"question":"Which AI is smarter overall?","answer":"As of 2026, both are highly capable. ChatGPT (GPT-4o) tends to perform better on creative and reasoning tasks, while Gemini excels at information retrieval and multimodal understanding. Benchmark results vary by specific task and update cycle."},{"question":"Can I use both for free?","answer":"Yes. Both offer free tiers with access to capable models. ChatGPT''s free tier uses GPT-4o mini with limited GPT-4o access. Gemini''s free tier uses Gemini 1.5 Flash with limited Pro access. Paid plans unlock full capabilities."},{"question":"Which AI handles images better?","answer":"Both generate and analyze images. ChatGPT uses DALL-E for generation and GPT-4V for analysis. Gemini uses Imagen for generation and has native multimodal understanding. Quality is comparable with different artistic styles."}]',
  'ChatGPT vs Gemini (2026): Honest Comparison',
  'ChatGPT vs Gemini compared as AI assistants. We evaluate writing, coding, integrations, and pricing to help you choose the right AI tool.'
);

-- 40. ChatGPT vs Perplexity
INSERT INTO comparisons (slug, category_slug, tool_a_id, tool_b_id, intro_content, verdict_content, migration_content, scenario_content, feature_matrix, faqs, meta_title, meta_description)
VALUES (
  'chatgpt-vs-perplexity',
  'ai-tools',
  (SELECT id FROM tools WHERE slug='chatgpt' LIMIT 1),
  (SELECT id FROM tools WHERE slug='perplexity' LIMIT 1),
  '<p>ChatGPT and Perplexity AI represent different visions for AI assistance. ChatGPT is a general-purpose AI assistant that excels at creative tasks, coding, analysis, and conversation. Perplexity AI positions itself as an AI-powered answer engine that combines real-time web search with AI synthesis to deliver cited, factual responses.</p><p>The distinction matters because these tools optimize for different outcomes. ChatGPT produces the most capable, flexible AI conversations. Perplexity produces the most reliable, source-backed answers to factual questions. Understanding this difference helps you use the right tool for each situation.</p><p>We compare both platforms on answer accuracy, source citation, creative capabilities, pricing, and the specific use cases where each tool delivers superior results.</p>',
  '<p>Choose ChatGPT for creative writing, coding, brainstorming, and tasks where you need a versatile AI partner for open-ended work. Choose Perplexity when you need factual, well-sourced answers with citations that you can verify, especially for research and information gathering.</p><p>ChatGPT wins as a creative AI assistant. Perplexity wins as an AI research and answer tool.</p>',
  '<p>Both tools are web-based services with no significant data migration needed. Chat histories are platform-specific and not transferable. Many professionals use both tools daily, switching based on the task at hand. Perplexity for research and fact-checking, ChatGPT for writing and creative work.</p>',
  '<ul><li><strong>Journalist fact-checking claims:</strong> Perplexity''s cited sources and real-time web access help journalists verify information quickly with traceable references.</li><li><strong>Marketer writing ad copy:</strong> ChatGPT''s creative writing and tone adjustment capabilities produce compelling marketing copy that Perplexity''s factual focus doesn''t match.</li><li><strong>Student researching a topic:</strong> Perplexity''s structured answers with academic sources and follow-up questions guide students through research efficiently.</li><li><strong>Developer building a feature:</strong> ChatGPT''s code generation, debugging assistance, and technical explanation capabilities make it the stronger development companion.</li></ul>',
  '[{"feature":"Free tier","category":"Pricing","toolAValue":"GPT-4o mini, limited GPT-4o","toolBValue":"Unlimited basic queries","winner":"b"},{"feature":"Premium pricing","category":"Pricing","toolAValue":"$20/mo ChatGPT Plus","toolBValue":"$20/mo Perplexity Pro","winner":"tie"},{"feature":"Source citations","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Optional web browsing","toolBValue":"Every answer includes sources","winner":"b"},{"feature":"Real-time information","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Available with browsing","toolBValue":"Always real-time by default","winner":"b"},{"feature":"Creative writing","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Excellent creative output","toolBValue":"Factual, not creative-focused","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Coding assistance","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Strong code generation","toolBValue":"Can help but not specialized","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Follow-up questions","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Conversational follow-ups","toolBValue":"Suggested related questions","winner":"tie"},{"feature":"Image generation","category":"Core","toolAValue":"DALL-E built-in","toolBValue":"Not available natively","winner":"a"}]',
  '[{"question":"Is Perplexity more accurate than ChatGPT?","answer":"For factual questions, Perplexity tends to be more reliable because it grounds every answer in real-time web sources that you can verify. ChatGPT can be equally accurate but may occasionally generate plausible-sounding information without source backing."},{"question":"Can Perplexity write content like ChatGPT?","answer":"Perplexity can generate text but it is optimized for informational answers, not creative content. For blog posts, marketing copy, fiction, or any creative writing, ChatGPT produces significantly better results."},{"question":"Should I subscribe to both?","answer":"If you frequently do both research and creative work, having both subscriptions offers genuine value. Perplexity Pro provides deeper research capabilities while ChatGPT Plus unlocks full creative and coding potential. Many knowledge workers find both worth the investment."}]',
  'ChatGPT vs Perplexity (2026): Honest Comparison',
  'ChatGPT vs Perplexity compared as AI tools. We evaluate accuracy, citations, creative writing, and pricing to help you choose the right AI assistant.'
);

-- 41. Claude vs Gemini
INSERT INTO comparisons (slug, category_slug, tool_a_id, tool_b_id, intro_content, verdict_content, migration_content, scenario_content, feature_matrix, faqs, meta_title, meta_description)
VALUES (
  'claude-vs-gemini',
  'ai-tools',
  (SELECT id FROM tools WHERE slug='claude' LIMIT 1),
  (SELECT id FROM tools WHERE slug='gemini' LIMIT 1),
  '<p>Claude and Gemini represent two of the most capable AI assistants available, each backed by different AI research philosophies. Claude, developed by Anthropic, emphasizes safety, thoughtfulness, and nuanced reasoning with notably strong performance on long-form analysis and coding tasks. Gemini, developed by Google, leverages deep integration with Google''s vast data and product ecosystem.</p><p>While both handle a broad range of tasks, their personalities and strengths differ meaningfully. Claude tends to produce more considered, detailed responses with strong analytical reasoning. Gemini excels at real-time information retrieval and seamless integration with Google Workspace tools that billions of people use daily.</p><p>We compare these AI assistants on reasoning quality, features, pricing, ecosystem integration, and the practical scenarios where each tool delivers the most value.</p>',
  '<p>Choose Claude if you value thoughtful, detailed responses, need strong coding and analysis capabilities, and appreciate an AI that handles nuance and complex instructions exceptionally well. Choose Gemini if you live in Google''s ecosystem and want AI that enhances Gmail, Docs, Search, and your Android device natively.</p><p>Claude wins on reasoning depth and analysis. Gemini wins on ecosystem integration and real-time information.</p>',
  '<p>Switching between AI assistants requires no data migration since conversations are independent on each platform. Custom prompts and workflows can be adapted between tools with minor adjustments. Many users maintain access to both, using each for its strengths. Claude''s API and Gemini''s API have different structures but similar capabilities for developers building applications.</p>',
  '<ul><li><strong>Analyst processing long documents:</strong> Claude''s large context window and strong reasoning capabilities make it excellent at summarizing, analyzing, and extracting insights from lengthy documents.</li><li><strong>Google Workspace user needing AI help:</strong> Gemini''s native integration with Gmail, Google Docs, Sheets, and Slides provides contextual AI assistance within the tools you already use.</li><li><strong>Developer writing and reviewing code:</strong> Claude''s coding capabilities are highly regarded, with strong performance on code generation, debugging, and code review across multiple programming languages.</li><li><strong>Student needing research help:</strong> Gemini''s Google Search integration provides current, source-backed information for academic research and learning.</li></ul>',
  '[{"feature":"Free tier","category":"Pricing","toolAValue":"Claude 3.5 Sonnet limited","toolBValue":"Gemini 1.5 Flash, limited Pro","winner":"tie"},{"feature":"Premium pricing","category":"Pricing","toolAValue":"$20/mo Claude Pro","toolBValue":"$20/mo Gemini Advanced","winner":"tie"},{"feature":"Reasoning depth","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Exceptionally nuanced analysis","toolBValue":"Strong but less detailed","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Context window","category":"Core","toolAValue":"200K tokens","toolBValue":"1M+ tokens","winner":"b"},{"feature":"Coding ability","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Excellent code generation","toolBValue":"Good, improving steadily","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Real-time web access","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Limited web access","toolBValue":"Native Google Search","winner":"b"},{"feature":"Ecosystem integration","category":"Integration","toolAValue":"API, limited integrations","toolBValue":"Full Google Workspace suite","winner":"b"},{"feature":"Safety and alignment","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Safety-focused by design","toolBValue":"Google AI safety framework","winner":"a"}]',
  '[{"question":"Which AI is better for coding?","answer":"Claude is widely regarded as one of the strongest AI coding assistants, particularly for complex code generation, refactoring, and code review. Gemini handles coding tasks competently but is generally considered a step behind Claude and ChatGPT in this area."},{"question":"Can both AI tools access the internet?","answer":"Gemini has native Google Search integration for real-time web access. Claude has more limited web access capabilities. For queries requiring current information, Gemini has a clear advantage."},{"question":"Which AI handles longer documents better?","answer":"Both have large context windows, with Gemini supporting 1M+ tokens and Claude supporting 200K tokens. Despite the smaller window, Claude is often praised for better comprehension and analysis of long documents within its context limit."}]',
  'Claude vs Gemini (2026): Honest Comparison',
  'Claude vs Gemini compared as AI assistants. We evaluate reasoning, coding, integrations, and pricing to help you pick the right AI for your work.'
);

-- 42. Grammarly vs Jasper
INSERT INTO comparisons (slug, category_slug, tool_a_id, tool_b_id, intro_content, verdict_content, migration_content, scenario_content, feature_matrix, faqs, meta_title, meta_description)
VALUES (
  'grammarly-vs-jasper',
  'ai-tools',
  (SELECT id FROM tools WHERE slug='grammarly' LIMIT 1),
  (SELECT id FROM tools WHERE slug='jasper' LIMIT 1),
  '<p>Grammarly and Jasper AI both enhance writing with artificial intelligence, but they serve completely different stages of the writing process. Grammarly is a writing assistant that checks grammar, spelling, tone, and clarity in real time across virtually any text input. Jasper is an AI content generation platform that creates marketing copy, blog posts, and brand content from scratch.</p><p>The distinction is editing versus creating. Grammarly makes your existing writing better by catching errors and suggesting improvements. Jasper generates new content based on your prompts, brand voice, and marketing objectives. Understanding this difference is essential for choosing the right tool.</p><p>We compare both platforms on their AI capabilities, use cases, pricing, integrations, and the value each delivers for individuals and marketing teams.</p>',
  '<p>Choose Grammarly if you need an always-on writing assistant that improves your grammar, clarity, and tone across email, documents, and web applications. Choose Jasper if you need an AI content generator that produces marketing copy, blog drafts, and social media content at scale from prompts and brand guidelines.</p><p>Grammarly wins for editing and polishing. Jasper wins for content creation and marketing scale.</p>',
  '<p>These tools serve different purposes and aren''t typically migrated between. Many teams use both simultaneously since Grammarly polishes the content that Jasper generates. Brand voice guidelines and templates in Jasper are platform-specific. Grammarly''s style guides and tone profiles stay within Grammarly. Teams adopting either tool can get started immediately.</p>',
  '<ul><li><strong>Professional improving daily emails:</strong> Grammarly''s browser extension and desktop integration catch errors and suggest tone improvements in emails, messages, and documents across all platforms.</li><li><strong>Marketing team scaling content production:</strong> Jasper''s templates, brand voice, and campaign features help marketing teams produce large volumes of on-brand content efficiently.</li><li><strong>Non-native English speaker:</strong> Grammarly''s grammar correction, vocabulary suggestions, and fluency improvements help non-native speakers communicate professionally in English.</li><li><strong>E-commerce brand writing product descriptions:</strong> Jasper''s product description templates and brand voice settings generate consistent, compelling copy for large product catalogs.</li></ul>',
  '[{"feature":"Core function","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Writing improvement/editing","toolBValue":"Content generation/creation","winner":"tie"},{"feature":"Free plan","category":"Pricing","toolAValue":"Basic grammar and spelling","toolBValue":"No free plan (7-day trial)","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Premium pricing","category":"Pricing","toolAValue":"$12/mo Premium","toolBValue":"$49/mo Creator","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Grammar checking","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Industry-leading accuracy","toolBValue":"Basic AI grammar assistance","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Content generation","category":"Core","toolAValue":"GrammarlyGO suggestions","toolBValue":"Full AI content creation suite","winner":"b"},{"feature":"Brand voice","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Tone detection and adjustment","toolBValue":"Custom brand voice training","winner":"b"},{"feature":"Browser extension","category":"Integration","toolAValue":"Works everywhere you write","toolBValue":"Chrome extension available","winner":"a"},{"feature":"Template library","category":"Core","toolAValue":"Not applicable","toolBValue":"50+ marketing templates","winner":"b"}]',
  '[{"question":"Can Grammarly generate content like Jasper?","answer":"Grammarly''s GrammarlyGO feature can generate short text suggestions and rewrites, but it''s not designed for creating long-form content from scratch. For full content generation, Jasper is significantly more capable."},{"question":"Should I use both Grammarly and Jasper?","answer":"Yes, they complement each other well. Use Jasper to generate draft content and Grammarly to polish, proofread, and improve the output. Many marketing teams use this combination to produce high-quality content at scale."},{"question":"Which tool is better for SEO content?","answer":"Jasper offers SEO-focused templates and integrates with Surfer SEO for keyword optimization during content creation. Grammarly doesn''t have SEO features. For SEO content creation, Jasper is the clear choice."}]',
  'Grammarly vs Jasper (2026): Honest Comparison',
  'Grammarly vs Jasper AI compared for writing. We evaluate editing, content generation, pricing, and features to help you choose the right AI writing tool.'
);
